INSERT INTO reference_documents (doc_name, page_number, content) VALUES
  ('Epic-Standards', 1, 'What is an Epic?  An Epic is a strategic body of work that delivers value in the form of a new product, product  capability, or outcome.  Epics correlate to an initiative''s business outcomes and contribute to the parent objective''s  success metric and key result achievement.  Epics in Aha! represent multiple tactical features that collectively deliver an increment of  value.  Here at Mastercard, our products are Epic and answer the Why, How, and Who of value  creation.  Mastercard Backlog Structure  Epic Principles  •   Product Managers and PM - Ts must use Problem Statements to define and quantify a  problem space, ecosystem, desired value/outcomes, and Mastercard benefit.  •   Product Managers and PM - Ts must own and manage Epics in Aha to ensure  accurate   Objective ,   Initiative,   and   Product   alignment.  o   All Epics in Aha! must map to a Mastercard Catalog Product in the Product  field in Aha!'),
  ('Epic-Standards', 2, '•   Epics must align with a Program Objective Success Metric and the Epic''s  description in Aha! must convey how an Epic''s delivery contributes to Program  Objective Success Metric achievement.  o   Click   here   to learn more about Program Objective Success Metrics.  •   Product Managers and PM - Ts partner with Engineering Managers, TPMs, and  Technical SMEs to decompose Epics into features that create incremental value.  o   An Epic''s Features must include all functional and non - functional stories  needed to deliver the Epic''s intended outcome or value.  o   Click   here   to learn more about   KTLO, BAU, and Technical Debt .  •   Product Managers and PM - Ts must partner with Engineering Managers, TPMs, and  Technical SMEs to:  o   Estimate an Epic''s high - level scope, duration, and LOE (Level of Effort) in T -  Shirt sizes.  ▪   Capture Estimates in the Preliminary Estimate Field in Aha!  o   Identify, negotiate, and sequence an Epic''s dependencies,  ▪   Click   here   to learn more about   Dependencies .  •   Product Managers and PM - Ts must analyze, refine, and prioritize three to six months  of epics during a recurring Program Review and Refinement event to ensure a  continuous flow of value creation.  o   Click   here   to learn more about   Prioritization .  •   Program Co - Founders, Owners, Product Managers, and PM - Ts must use  the   Strategic Alignment & Flow   dashboard to govern Strategy and tactical  Alignment, Roadmap Health, and Epic data.  Epic Guidelines  Epic Ideation  Product Managers and PM - Ts partner with Engineering, Delivery leaders, and Technical  SMEs to capture an Epic’s Description of Work, Value Statement, Assumptions, Definition  of Done, and what is Out of Scope to inform refinement and decomposition discussion s.'),
  ('Epic-Standards', 3, 'Consider using one of the below methods to inform Epic Descriptions in Aha!  Problem Statement : A synopsis that conveys how a product, service, or outcome meets a  customer''s or user''s needs better than its competitor or previous versions.  Epic Story :   Leveraging user story format, draft a story that conveys the Epic requirements  on a high level to help Product, Engineering, Delivery Leaders, and Technical SMEs  understand the opportunity problem space and ideate potential features.  Click   here   for   Epic Ideation Guidance .  Capturing Epics in Aha!  Leverage the Epic description field in Aha to capture Epic ideation outcomes,  Technology Program Example  What   Why   How  Description of  Work   Epic Story or Statement  The Authorization Platform uses network manag  system or network events or tasks. These messa  communicate network status conditions. Netwo  be customer - initiated or Authorization Platf orm -  Typical uses of customer - initiated network man  following:  •   Sign in to and sign out from the Authoriza  •   Activate or deactivate socket connection'),
  ('Epic-Standards', 4, '•   Request network connection status  •   Perform encryption key management tas  Typical uses of system - initiated network manag  following:  •   Request network connection status  •   Perform encryption key management tas  The objective of this epic is to build out the targe  Connectivity Status Management application in  landscape. Although we will be using the moder  to support the current systems and re plicate the  network management application. The intention  current mainframe network connectivity applica  once the new solution is tested and working.  Value  Statement   Convey Epic outcome value  Problem Statement:  For   <Issuers that need to be signed on to the net  Who   <Use Authorization Platform for Banknet, M  The   < Network Connectivity Status Management  Is a   <solution>  That   <handles customer or system - initiated   Net  messages>  Unlike   <today''s mainframe network manageme  Our Solution   < Supports Dual Message Switch.  impact due to SISO (sign on sign off) being hand  application.   Customers will not be asked to sign  into the new system. Migration should all happe  impacting the customers.>  Assumptions   Provide transparency   into the  known - unknown Product,  •   We will be processing the 0800 network m  messages and respond with the 0810 to t'),
  ('Epic-Standards', 5, '(Coming  Soon)  Engineering or Delivery risk that  may impede value delivery.  •   NCSM app needs to be able to replace th  connectivity application so it can be deco  •   NCSM app needs to listen to broadcasts  intermediate phase when both are runnin  •   NCSM app needs to send the sign on stat  system''s MIPs  •   There is no need to share sign on status a  Definition of  Done   Desired Epic Outcomes  1.   NCSM application is live on production fo  Satellite  2.   NCSM application deployed in the Europ  connectivity for on - soil Nexus  3.   NCSM application deployed in central sit  (banknet) and be a replacement for main  application  4.   Handling of 0800 sign on / off messages b  5.   Sequence Diagrams and Documentation  6.   Functional logs documentation is availab  searchable in dashboard  7.   Full test coverage with test results posted  8.   Performance testing done  9.   Feature Demos completed  Out of Scope   Convey value not being delivered  •   Migrate Sign on / off capabilities off main  o   This epic will focus on building ou  mirroring the connectivity statues  mainframe application to prepare  •   Sign on for Acquirers  o   Ability to source messages to onli'),
  ('Epic-Standards', 6, '▪   Online Clearing Acquirers w  credentials  ▪   Need to know the routes to  ▪   Start storing sign on status  •   System generated echo tests  o   Customers can request the Maste  probe via echo test to make sure c  o   This is currently not set up in the c  •   Upgrading the SA solution to using this m  o   We want to get to this quickly, but  modernized state first with Europe  Estimation  Product Managers and PM - Ts must partner with Engineering Managers, TPMs, and  Technical SMEs to explore and analyze Epic requirements to surface the Epic’s Preliminary  T - Shirt size when Epics are Exploring status.  T - Shirt Size   Iterations/Sprints  S   3 - 4  M   5 - 6  L   7 - 8  Iteration or Sprint = 2 Weeks'),
  ('Epic-Standards', 7, 'Epics that require 8+ Iterations/Sprints must be decomposed into smaller Epics that align  with the above T - Shirt Size Guidelines.  Decomposition  Epics are decomposed into tactical features with benefit hypothesis statements and  stories that meet INVEST.  Program Leaders must partner to ensure Epic Features'' concurrent delivery in at most   16  weeks   during a recurring Refinement Event.  Click   here   for Decomposition guidance.  MVP Definition & Studio''s Prototype Phase  What:   An MVP (Minimum Viable Product) is a   first version   of a product, service or outcome  that has enough features to attract customers, validate expected behaviors, and use  customer feedback to inform later versions.  Why:   Validate the intended   customer experience with customers and distribution partners  to surface issues, bugs and other later version enhancements.  How:   Identify just enough Epics to satisfy external or internal customer needs and  establish an early adopter feedback mechanism to inform subsequent solution versions.  Click   here   for MVP Definition guidance.'),
  ('Epic-Standards', 8, 'Epic Lifecycle, Status Designations & Confidence Intervals  Product Managers and PM - Ts are responsible for ensuring Aha Epic status lifecycle  designation accuracy.  Epic Lifecyle Status Designations  Each Epic Status designation maps to our Confidence Intervals  ( Low [12+ Months Out], Medium [6 - 12 Months Out] and High [Now   -   6 Months Out] )'),
  ('Feature-Standard', 1, 'What is a Feature?  A feature is a function of a product or service that fulfills a market or internal customer  need.  Here at Mastercard, features are tactical and align to a product, service, or outcome.  Showcasing a feature’s value is essential to ensuring appropriate prioritization.  Epics are comprised of multiple features that collectively deliver value.  Feature Principles  •   Features must be associated with a Strategic Epic in Aha! that is visible on a  Program or Product Strategy Roadmap.  •   Product and Engineering leaders must own their program’s features; leaders  collaborate to define each feature’s body of work, and acceptance criteria   –   on a  high level.  •   External program dependencies must be considered when estimating a tactical  feature’s Level of Effort (LOE) and duration.  •   Features must be agreed upon by all program professionals in order to meet the  Definition of Ready to work.'),
  ('Feature-Standard', 2, '•   Features must include all functional and non - functional work items necessary to  deliver value in accordance with the feature’s Definition of Done and Acceptance  Criteria  •   Product Backlogs must contain at least 2 Iterations of elaborated features/stories,  aligned to the appropriate Strategic Epic in Aha!; ensuring optimal backlog health.  •   Features should remain in the Product Backlog until prioritized; prioritized features  must progress through the feature lifecycle in the work management tool.  •   Feature ‘State’ must stay aligned to underlying stories.  •   Features that are the In - Progress, Staging, and Done must have a program Product  captured in the required Product field to save changes.  •   Click   here   for Feature &   Product Association guidance.  •   Features must state the user problem or hypothesis  •   Feature Acceptance Criteria should align with the parent Epic’s Definition of Done  Feature Guidelines  Writing a Feature  Aha! and ALM are integrated; strategical Epics in Aha! are automatically sent to ALM as  Tactical Epics.  Programs must capture feature business hypothesis statements in ALM since tactical  Epics in ALM house traditional feature descriptors,  •   Description of Work  •   Value Statement  •   Definition of Done  Product and Engineering leaders must partner with program members to write feature  benefits hypothesis and acceptance criteria before decomposing a feature into stories, as  a program or team, during a recurring Refinement event.  Benefit Hypothesis  A feature’s benefit hypothesis conveys each feature requirement’s benefit.'),
  ('Feature-Standard', 3, 'Here are two benefit hypothesis statement, click   here   to learn how to write effective feature  benefit hypothesis statements.  Feature   Benefit Hypothesis  In - Service  software update  If we update to version 7.1 then we will significantly reduce planned  downtime by 10%  Hardware VPN  acceleration  We believe less network intrusions will be achieved if 7200 series routers  successfully achieve High - Performance encryption for secure WAN with  Virtual Private Network Acceleration Module 2+ upgrade.  Acceptance Criteria  A feature’s acceptance criteria conveys the behavior, benefit or result necessary to be  accepted by a user, internal/external customer, or system.  Product Owners (PMT) use Acceptance Criteria to validate feature implementation  accuracy and the desired value add / benefit.  A feature’s Acceptance Criteria must convey the following, at minimum,  •   All feature stories are delivered and accepted.  •   Feature benefit hypothesis has been validated.  Decomposing Features  •   Product and Engineering Leaders should partner with Program members to  decompose features into actionable user stories during a recurring Refinement  event.  •   Click   here   for Feature decomposition guidance.  Estimating Features'),
  ('Feature-Standard', 4, '•   Ideally, feature estimates are an aggregate of the underlying story estimates since  features are a grouping of stories.  Future State Q4 2024  •   In ALM, features are estimated by T - Shirt sizes captured in the Preliminary Estimate  field on the feature record.  T Shirt Size   Person Week (s)   Description  Extra Small   3  One full time program  three weeks, or three  feature in one week.  Small   6  One full time program  weeks, or six program  one week.  Medium   9  One full time program  nine weeks, or nine p  feature in one week.  Large   15  One full time program  fifteen weeks, or fifte  feature in one week.'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 1, 'The Lighthouse  Alberta  Exported on 2026 - 03 - 05 11:44:46'),
