  ('The_Lighthouse', 36, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   36  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  given  customer  using client  config from  TCS service  with the one  configured for that  customer in client  config from TCS  Service  Then   reject the  entire batch request  and return the  response as 400 bad  request with  " ProvisioningType  mismatch error"  bps - enr -  val.007.enroll.validations.external -  consumer - id.format  CURRENT  Validate the  format of  external -  consumer - id  of the  consumers in  batch using  the program  capability  configured in  TCS service  Given   a request is  received for batch  enrollment of cards  When   any of the  consumer record in  the   request contains  an external -  consumer - id which  doesn''t meet the  formatting  requirements  specified for the  program capability in  TCS Service  Then   update the  batch status as failed  and with reason  description  1.   Initial  version  under  Project  Lighthouse  bps - enr -  val.008.enroll.validations.external -  card - id.format  CURRENT  Validate the  format of  external - card -  id of the cards  in batch using  the program  capability  configured in  TCS service  Given   a request is  received for batch  enrollment of cards  When   any of the  card record in the  request contains an  external - card - id  which doesn''t meet  the formatting  requirements  specified for the  program capability in  TCS Service  Then   update the  batch status as failed  and with reason  description  1.   Initial  version  under  Project  Lighthouse'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 37, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   37  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  bps - enr -  val.009.enroll.validations.linked -  identities.structure  CURRENT  Validate the  structure of  Linked  Identities the  consumers in  batch  Given   a request is  received for batch  enrollment of cards  When   any of the  consumer record in  the   request contains  an invalid linked  identity structure like  -   mismatching type  and value e.g..  EMAIL type with  MOBILE value,  MOBILE type with  EMAIL, unknown  identity type etc.  Then   update the  batch status as failed  and with reason  description  1.   Initial  version  under  Project  Lighthouse  3.3.10.2   Defaults  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  bps - enr -  def.001.enroll.defaults.bulk -  provisioning - type  CURRENT  Enrollment  should be  shared in the  issuer directory  by default if not  passed by the  customer  Given   a request is  received for batch  enrollment of cards  When   bulk - provisioning -  type is not passed by  customer  Then   default the type to  AUTO_ENABLEMENT  1.   Initial  version  under  Project  Lighthouse  3.3.10.3   Conflicts  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  3.3.10.4   Business Logic  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  bps - enr -  blo.001.enroll.business -  logic.re - submitted - batch  CURRENT  If customer re -  submits the  previously  submitted batch  Given   a request is  received for batch  enrollment of cards  When   the batch  already exists in the  1.   Initial version  under  Project  Lighthouse'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 38, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   38  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  again, return the  same batch details  without processing  it as a new batch  system with the  combination of same  external - batch - id, src -  client - id and service - id  coming from the  request  Then   return the 202  Accepted response  AND include same  batch - id and external -  batch - id of existing  batch in the response  WITHOUT processing  it as a new batch  3.3.10.5   KPI Events  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  3.3.10.6   Successful Requests  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  3.4   Checkout Service Dashboard  3.4.1   Table of Contents  •   Overview  •   Dependencies  •   Endpoints & behavior  o   Swagger  ▪   B2B endpoint  ▪   Confirmations endpoint  ▪   Composite checkout endpoint  ▪   Guest checkout endpoint  •   Service Capabilities and configurations  •   High - Level Design Artifacts  •   Current Performance Metrics  •   Technical Roadmap  •   Technical Infrastructure'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 39, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   39  •   Team and ALM  3.4.2   Overview  •   Description:  Checkout Service is a program sensitive orchestration service within the MACS that  manages appropriate Checkout payload composition.  o   This orchestration service is primarily responsible for handling the creation of  payload with in the MACs system with the Dynamic Data Cryptogram or DTVC  for secure transactions. It comprises of other services like Composite Checkout  Service and Credential   Dispatcher Service. It interacts with other downstream  platform services and does the validation of the request based on the program  rules configured for the different clients and serves the payload.  o   Composite Checkout Service is a super orchestration layer that is built  specifically for Apple Batch Checkout use cases. It calls the profile for enroll as  well the Checkout based on the request type.  o   Credentials Dispatcher Service is responsible for pushing the payload to BND  asynchronously and BND would in turn call the third party SRCI using the Make  Payment API.  o   SRC Core (Code name   -   Alberta) is a EMVCo standards - based checkout  solution for browser - based & in - app payments, providing a consistent  consumer journey for ecommerce, where every card is secured through  network tokenization and every transaction is authen ticated through 3 - D  Secure. SRC is built upon EMVCo industry standards including the EMV®  Secure Remote Commerce Technical Framework (SRC), the EMV® Payment  Tokenization Specification   –   Technical Framework, and the updated EMV® 3 - D  Secure Protocol and Core   Functions Specification.  o   This browser - based checkout is usually referred as Clickto - Pay (C2P). C2P  provides a comprehensive set of checkout services including (but not limited to)  performing the role of a Digital Card Facilitator (DCF) and SRCi, providing a  Mastercard implementati on that integrates with the SRC System(s), allows for  authentication of the cardholder and opportunity for the merchant to obtain  fraud liability shift to the issuer, enables the creation and storage of a Payment  Token, generated by either the Mastercard D igital Enablement Service (MDES)  or an approved Third -   Party Token Service Provider (TSP), including use of  dynamic data in each transaction to enforce token domain restriction controls,  exposes secure interfaces to Digital Shopping Applications (DSAs) suc h as  Merchants, and SRC Initiators such as Payment Service Providers to perform  payments, and provides consistent user experiences for checkout including the  display of issuer card art.  o   Apart from supporting browser - based eCommerce checkout transactions, SRC  also enables Merchants & other clients to use Card - On - File (COF) for  checkouts. This feature is generally referred as SCOF   - Secure Card - On - File.  All of our SCOF functions are exposed   to our clients via B2B APIs, that are  protected either using MTLS or OAuth.  ▪   The clients that use this function are broadly classified into 2 types:  •   • S4C   –   SRC for Device based clients ( etc. Apple Pay)  •   •   S4M   –   SRC for Merchants / Processors (Adyen / Paypal)  o   Both C2P & SCOF flows tie into the Mastercard Authorization flow via a  component called Merchant Binding & Verification Service (aka MBVS). MBVS  is a PCF app, that is part of the SRC ecosystem, which binds Merchants with  Cryptograms / Tokens submitted by A cquirers. The main purpose of this'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 40, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   40  binding is to improve fraud detection by ensuring that the token / cryptograms in  the transaction belong to the Merchant.  o   SCOF flows produce certain notification events that are pushed to the clients  using a component called Business Notification Dispatcher (BND). BND is  another PCF app, that is part of SRC ecosystem, which notifies the client on  these events. Some of the cri tical events sent back to the clients are: • NTU  (Notify Token Update)   –   A card lifecycle update event (such as card  successfully tokenized, or card reported as lost etc.) • TDS (Transaction Detail  Service)   –   A TDS event is triggered when a enrolled / toke nized card is used for  a transaction.  •   Purpose & Scope:  Checkout is the action of a Consumer completing a purchase with a given card. This  includes two general use cases:  o   Creating and (optionally) returning transaction credentials so that payment can  be made.  o   Confirming a payment has been executed.  Checkout provides the means to execute these two steps. It is initiated at the DCF and  completed at the SRCI. The service also incorporates Checkout as a Guest.  SRC Checkout Orchestration Service provides endpoints for Creating Transactions and  generating Transaction Tokens that facilitate performing the transaction. It is the  orchestration layer for DCF and SRCi to enable checkout workflow with digital platform  s ervices (e.g. consumer - service, address - service, card - service, etc.) and other shared -  services (e.g. CaaS)  Refer to the following EMVCO Version -   EMVCo - Secure - Remote - Commerce - Specifications -  API - 1.0  For all draft versions of EMVCO refer to  -   https://fusion.mastercard.int/confluence/display/alberta/EMVCo+SRC+API+Spec  3.4.3   Dependencies  This table lists and describes all services or systems that provide input or trigger events for this  microservice or rely on data or functionalities from this microservice.  Service Name   Type   Service Dashboard  Pre - Checkout   Upstream  Middleware   Upstream  Composite Checkout   Upstream  External Clients (e.g. MCI,MPGS, POP)   Upstream  TCS   Downstream  PI Core   Downstream  Consumer Service   Downstream'),
