  ('The_Lighthouse', 54, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   54  3.5.10   Consumer service : Behavior : [POST /consumers/searches]  •   Consumer search  o   consumer.searches.01  o   consumer.searches.02  o   consumer.searches.03  o   consumer.searches.04  o   consumer.searches.05  o   consumer.searches.06  o   consumer.searches.07  o   consumer.searches.08  o   consumer.searches.09  o   consumer.searches.10  o   consumer.searches.11  3.5.10.1   Consumer search  Behavior ID   Title   Behavior   Change Log  feature/Story  Reference  (in order   -  latest first)  consumer.searches.01   Search by Email   Given the user knows the  consumer''s email address  and related program IDs  (e.g., ''SCOF'', ''C2P'')  When the user inputs the  email address  Then the system retrieves  consumer details with  pagination  consumer.searches.02   Search by Consumer  ID  Given the user knows the  consumer ID and related  program IDs  When the user inputs the  consumer ID  Then the system retrieves  consumer details with  pagination  consumer.searches.03   Search by Mobile  Number with Country  Code  Given the user knows the  mobile number with country  code and related program  IDs  When the user inputs the  mobile number with country  code  Then the system retrieves  consumer details with  pagination'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 55, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   55  Behavior ID   Title   Behavior   Change Log  feature/Story  Reference  (in order   -  latest first)  consumer.searches.04   Search by Hashed  Email  Given the user knows the  hashed email and related  program IDs  When the user inputs the  hashed email  Then the system retrieves  consumer details with  pagination  consumer.searches.05   Search by Hashed  Mobile Number with  Country Code  Given the user knows the  hashed mobile number with  country code and related  program IDs  When the user inputs the  hashed mobile number with  country code  Then the system retrieves  consumer details with  pagination  consumer.searches.06   Search by Hashed  Email and Hashed  Mobile Number with  Country Code  Given the user knows both  the hashed email and  hashed mobile number with  country code and related  program IDs  When the user inputs both  hashed email and hashed  mobile number with country  code  Then the system retrieves  consumer details with  pagination  consumer.searches.07   Search by Multiple  Hashed Emails  Given the user knows  multiple hashed emails and  related program IDs  When the user inputs  multiple hashed emails  Then the system retrieves  consumer details with  pagination  consumer.searches.08   Search by Multiple  Hashed Mobile  Numbers with Country  Code  Given the user knows  multiple hashed mobile  numbers with country code  and related program IDs  When the user inputs  multiple hashed mobile  numbers with country code  Then the system retrieves  consumer details with  pagination  consumer.searches.09   Search by Multiple  Pairs of Hashed Emails  Given the user knows  multiple pairs of hashed'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 56, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   56  Behavior ID   Title   Behavior   Change Log  feature/Story  Reference  (in order   -  latest first)  and Hashed Mobile  Numbers with Country  Code  emails and hashed mobile  numbers with country code  and related program IDs  When the user inputs  multiple pairs of hashed  emails and hashed mobile  numbers with country code  Then the system retrieves  consumer details with  pagination  consumer.searches.10   Search by Hashed  Email or Hashed  Mobile Number with  Country Code or  Combinations thereof  Given the user knows either  hashed email or hashed  mobile number with country  code or combinations  thereof and related program  IDs  When the user inputs either  hashed email or hashed  mobile number with country  code  Then the system retrieves  consumer details with  pagination  consumer.searches.11   Search by Hashed  Email and/or Hashed  Mobile Number with  Country Code  Given the user knows  combinations of hashed  emails and/or hashed  mobile numbers with  country code and related  program IDs  When the user inputs  combinations of hashed  emails and/or hashed  mobile numbers with  country code  Then the system retrieves  consumer details with  pagination  3.5.11   Consumer Service : Behaviors :  [DELETE/directories/{directory - id}/consumers/{consumer - id}]  •   Validations  o   dir - cns - del - val.001.delete - directory - consumer.validations.directory -  id.mandatory  o   dir - cns - del - val.002.delete - directory - consumer.validations.consumer -  id.mandatory  o   dir - cns - del - val.003.delete - directory - consumer.validations.type.possible - values  •   Defaults'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 57, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   57  o   dir - cns - del - def.001.delete - directory - consumer.defaults.parameters.type  •   Business Logic  o   dir - cns - del - blo.001.delete - directory - consumer.business - logic.consumer - data  o   dir - cns - del - blo.002.delete - directory - consumer.business - logic.litigation - hold  o   dir - cns - del - blo.003.delete - directory - consumer.business - logic.delete - with -  external - consumer - id  o   dir - cns - del - blo.004.delete - directory - consumer.business - logic.delete - with -  directory - consumer - id  o   dir - cns - del - blo.005.delete - directory - consumer.business - logic.non - existent -  account  •   KPI Events  o   dir - cns - del - kpi.001.delete - directory - consumer.kpi.started  o   dir - cns - del - kpi.002.delete - directory - consumer.kpi.failed  o   dir - cns - del - kpi.003.delete - directory - consumer.kpi.completed  •   Successful Requests  3.5.11.1   Validations  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  dir - cns - del - val.001.delete - directory -  consumer.validations.directory -  id.mandatory  PROPOSED  Consumer in  directory  cannot be  deleted without  a directory - id  Given   a delete  consumer  request is  received in a  directory  When   request  doesn''t have a  directory - id  Then   reject the  request and  return the  response as 400  bad request  1.   XID story  reference  dir - cns - del - val.002.delete - directory -  consumer.validations.consumer -  id.mandatory  PROPOSED  Consumer in  directory  cannot be  deleted without  a consumer - id  Given   a delete  consumer  request is  received in a  directory  When   request  doesn''t have a  consumer - id  Then   reject the  request and  return the  response as 400  bad request  1.   XID story  reference'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 58, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   58  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  dir - cns - del - val.003.delete - directory -  consumer.validations.type.possible -  values  PROPOSED  Consumer in  directory can  be deleted  using either  directory -  consumer - id or  external -  consumer - id  only  Given   a delete  consumer  request is  received in a  directory  When   request  contains a type  anything other  than directory -  consumer - id and  external -  consumer - id  Then   reject the  request and  return the  response as 400  bad request  1.   XID story  reference  3.5.11.2   Defaults  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  dir - cns - del - def.001.delete - directory -  consumer.defaults.parameters.type  PROPOSED  Consumer is  deleted using  directory -  consumer - id by  default  Given   a delete  consumer  request is  received in a  directory  When '' type''  parameter is  not specified in  request  Then   consumer  is deleted using  directory -  consumer - id by  default  1.   XID story  reference  3.5.11.3   Business Logic  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  dir - cns - del -  blo.001.delete - directory -  consumer.business -  logic.consumer - data  PROPOSED  Delete  consumer data  from all the  related tables  Given   a delete consumer  request is received in a  directory  When   matching consumer  record is found in a directory  Then   delete the consumer  record and associated meta  data from directory context only  i.e. delete consumer, delete all  the associated consent history,  1.   XID story  reference'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 59, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   59  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  delete all the associated  verification records, delete all  the associated throttle records  and delete all the associated  identities  dir - cns - del -  blo.002.delete - directory -  consumer.business -  logic.litigation - hold  PROPOSED  Do not allow  deletion of a  consumer held  up for litigation  Given   a delete consumer  request is received in a  directory  When   consumer is held up for  litigation  Then   don''t delete the  consumer and throw 500  internal server error  1.   XID story  reference  dir - cns - del -  blo.003.delete - directory -  consumer.business -  logic.delete - with - external -  consumer - id  PROPOSED  Delete a  consumer with  external -  consumer - id  Given   a delete consumer  request is received in a  directory  When   request is sent using  external - consumer - id  Then   search and delete a  consumer record using  external - consumer - id only (and  not using directory - consumer -  id)  1.   XID story  reference  dir - cns - del -  blo.004.delete - directory -  consumer.business -  logic.delete - with -  directory - consumer - id  PROPOSED  Delete a  consumer with  directory -  consumer - id  Given   a delete consumer  request is received in a  directory  When   request is sent using  directory - consumer - id  Then   search and delete a  consumer record using  directory - consumer - id only  (and not using external -  consumer - id)  1.   XID story  reference  dir - cns - del -  blo.005.delete - directory -  consumer.business -  logic.non - existent -  account  PROPOSED  Attempt to  delete a non  existent  consumer  Given   a delete consumer  request is received in a  directory  When   a matching   consumer  record is not found in a  directory  Then   return the 404 NOT  FOUND response  1.   XID story  reference  3.5.11.4   KPI Events'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 60, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   60  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  dir - cns - del - kpi.001.delete -  directory -  consumer.kpi.started  PROPOSED  Delete directory  consumer request  will publish the KPI  event for  ''STARTED''  Given   a delete  consumer request is  received in a directory  When   request is  processed  Then   publish the KPI  event for STARTED  state before starting any  processing to record the  start of the request   -  Directory 2.0 KPI  events  1.   XID story  reference  dir - cns - del - kpi.002.delete -  directory -  consumer.kpi.failed  PROPOSED  Delete directory  consumer request  will publish the KPI  event for ''FAILED''  Given   a delete  consumer request is  received in a directory  When   request gets  failed  Then   publish the KPI  event for FAILED to  record failure of the  request   -   Directory 2.0  KPI events  1.   XID story  reference  dir - cns - del - kpi.003.delete -  directory -  consumer.kpi.completed  PROPOSED  Delete directory  consumer request  will publish the KPI  event for  ''COMPLETED''  Given   a delete  consumer request is  received in a directory  When   request gets  completed  Then   publish the KPI  event for COMPLETED  to record completion of  the request   -   Directory  2.0 KPI events  1.   XID story  reference  3.5.11.5   Successful Requests  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  3.5.12   Consumer Service : Behaviors : [DELETE/program -  consumers/{consumer - id}]  •   Validations  o   pgm - cns - del - val.001.delete - program - consumer.validations.program -  id.mandatory'),
