  ('The_Lighthouse', 92, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   92  o   cns - cre - con - 017.create - consumer.companion.single - pii - consumer - with -  external - consumer - id.conflicts.email - and - mobile - and - external - consumer - id -  match - on - different - profiles  o   cns - cre - con - 018.create - consumer.companion.single - pii - consumer - with -  external - consumer - id.conflicts.external - consumer - id  •   Companion   -   Multi PII Conflicts  o   cns - cre - con - 001.create - consumer.companion.multi - pii -  consumer.conflicts.external - consumer - id - and - identities  o   dir - cns - cre - con.002.create - consumer.companion.multi - pii -  consumer.conflicts.external - consumer - id - and - identities  o   dir - cns - cre - con.003.create - consumer.companion.multi - pii -  consumer.conflicts.external - consumer - id - and - identities  o   dir - cns - cre - con.004.create - consumer.companion.multi - pii -  consumer.conflicts.external - consumer - id  o   dir - cns - cre - con.005.create - consumer.companion.multi - pii -  consumer.conflicts.external - consumer - id - and - identities  o   dir - cns - cre - con.006.create - consumer.companion.multi - pii -  consumer.conflicts.external - consumer - id - and - identities  3.5.17.1   Common Validations  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Chan  ge  Log  cns - cre - val - 001.create -  consumer.common.validations.progra  m - id.mandatory  CURRENT  Reject creation of  consumer without  program - id  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a  directory 1.0  When   consumer  doesn''t have  program - id  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as 400  bad request  cns - cre - val - 002.create -  consumer.common.validations.identitie  s.duplicates  CURRENT  Consumer with  duplicate identities  (emails/mobiles) is  not allowed  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a  directory 1.0  When   request is  having duplicate  identities  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as 400  bad request  cns - cre - val - 003.create -  consumer.common.validations.identitie  s.max - emails  CURRENT   Given   a consumer  creation request is'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 93, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   93  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Chan  ge  Log  Consumer exceeding  the email limit are not  permitted  received in a  directory 1.0  When   no of emails  exceeds the  configurable limit  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as 400  bad request  cns - cre - val - 004.create -  consumer.common.validations.identitie  s.max - mobiles  CURRENT  Consumer exceeding  the mobile limit are  not permitted  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a  directory 1.0  When   number of  ''mobiles phone  numbers''   exceeds  the configurable limit  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as 400  bad request  cns - cre - val - 005.create -  consumer.common.validations.identitie  s.email - format  CURRENT  Consumer having  email address not in  RFC 822 format   -   is  not allowed  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a  directory 1.0  When   email address  is not in RFC 822  format  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as 400  bad request  cns - cre - val - 006.create -  consumer.common.validations.identitie  s.mobile - format  CURRENT  Consumer with  mobile number which  doesn''t comply with  given regex  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a  directory 1.0  When   mobile number  doesn''t comply  with   Regex   -   "^[0 -  9]{4,14}$"  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as 400  bad request  cns - cre - val - 007.create -  consumer.common.validations.identitie  s.mobile - country - code - format  CURRENT  Consumer with  mobile country code  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a  directory 1.0'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 94, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   94  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Chan  ge  Log  which doesn''t comply  with given regex  When   mobile country  code doesn''t comply  with   Regex   -   "^[+]?[0 -  9]{1,4}$"  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as 400  bad request  cns - cre - val - 008.create -  consumer.common.validations.national  - id  CURRENT  National Id of the  consumer needs to  comply with  validations of region -  config - library  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a  directory 1.0  When   national id  doesn''t comply with  configurations  available in region  config library  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as 400  bad request  cns - cre - val - 008.create -  consumer.common.validations.status  CURRENT  Consumer can be  created either with  only  ''PENDING_VERIFIC  ATION'' or ''ACTIVE''  status  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a  directory 1.0  When   status is  neither  ''PENDING_VERIFIC  ATION'' nor ''ACTIVE''  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as 400  bad request  cns - cre - val - 009.create -  consumer.common.validations.preferre  d - email  CURRENT  Consumer can be  with at least one and  at max one preferred  email  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a  directory 1.0 with  emails  When   no preferred  email or more than  preferred emails are  received  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as 400  bad request  cns - cre - val - 010.create -  consumer.common.validations.preferre  d - mobile  CURRENT  Consumer can be  with at least one and  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 95, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   95  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Chan  ge  Log  at max one preferred  mobile  directory 1.0 with  mobiles  When   no preferred  mobile or more than  preferred mobiles are  received  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as 400  bad request  cns - cre - val - 011.create -  consumer.common.validations.external  - consumer - id.no - pii - data  CURRENT  Consumer cannot  have any PII data in  external - consumer - id  as it is stored in plain  text without  encryption and  upstream services  are expected to send  it in UUID format  without PII  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a  directory 1.0  When   external -  consumer - id contains  a PII data  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as 400  bad request  3.5.17.2   Common Business Logic  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Chang  e Log  cns - cre - blo - 001.create -  consumer.common.business -  logic.identities  CURRENT  Swagger should  automatically pick the  value object inside the  identities array based  on selected type field   -  If type is EMAIL, email  object should  automatically be  picked for value.  If type is MOBILE,  mobile object should  automatically be  picked for value.  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a directory 1.0  When   identities are  present  Then   even before  processing the request,  swagger should  automatically pick the  value object inside the  identities array based on  selected type field   -   If type  is EMAIL, email object  should automatically be  picked for value.  If type is MOBILE, mobile  object should automatically  be picked for value.  Reject the request if  mismatches found.'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 96, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   96  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Chang  e Log  cns - cre - blo - 002.create -  consumer.common.business -  logic.pii - data - storage  CURRENT  All PII data of the  consumer should be  stored only in  encrypted and  masked format in the  database. PII data  should not be stored  in plain text.  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a directory 1.0  When   PII data is present  Then   PII data is stored  only in encrypted and  masked format in the  database without storing in  the plain text  cns - cre - blo - 003.create -  consumer.common.business -  logic.consent - history  CURRENT  Create consent history  record for acceptance  of each of the consent  -   tnc_version,  privacy_policy_versio  n,  cookie_consent_versi  on,  consumer_protection_  version,  marketing_optin  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a directory 1.0  When   tnc_version,  privacy_policy_version,  cookie_consent_version,  consumer_protection_versi  on,  marketing_optin   consents  are accepted  Then   create a consent  history for each of the  consent and respective  version separately  cns - cre - blo - 004.create -  consumer.common.business -  logic.default_consumer_protecti  on_version  CURRENT  Create a consumer  with default  consumer_protection_  version if not received  in the request  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a directory 1.0  When   consumer_protectio  n_version is not specified  Then   create a consumer  with default  consumer_protection_versi  on internally  cns - cre - blo - 005.create -  consumer.common.business -  logic.email - marketing - support  CURRENT  Create a  marketing_optin  consent only if it  supported for a  program id  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a directory 1.0  When   marketing_optin is  specified  Then   create a  marketing_optin consent  only if it supported   Else   if  not supported, then create  a consumer without  marketing_optin even if it  is received in the request  cns - cre - blo.006.create -  consumer.business -  logic.common.litigation - hold  CURRENT  Request conflicts with  the consumer held up  for litigation  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a directory 1.0  When   it conflicts (based  on conflict rules) with the'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 97, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   97  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Chang  e Log  existing consumer within  the program id and that  consumer is held up for  litigation  Then   the consumer is not  recreated or conflict is not  returned. Instead   return  the 500 internal server  error  cns - cre - blo.007.create -  consumer.common.business -  logic.override - pending -  verification - on  CURRENT  Recreate consumer if  override - pending -  verification parameter  is true and consumer  is in  ''PENDING_VERIFICA  TION'' status  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a directory 1.0  When   it conflicts (based  on conflict rules) with the  existing consumer within  the program id and that  consumer is in  ''PENDING_VERIFICATIO  N'' status and override -  pending - verification  parameter is true  Then   recreate the  consumer record by  deleting existing record  and return a new record in  the response  cns - cre - blo.008.create -  consumer.common.business -  logic.override - pending -  verification - off  CURRENT  Don''t recreate  consumer if override -  pending - verification  parameter is false  even if consumer is in  ''PENDING_VERIFICA  TION'' status  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a directory 1.0  When   it conflicts (based  on conflict rules) with the  existing consumer within  the program id and  override - pending -  verification parameter is  false  Then   return 409 conflict  based on conflict rules  cns - cre - blo - 009.create -  consumer.common.business -  logic.set - create - time - stamp  CURRENT  Record create time for  audit purpose  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a directory 1.0  When   request qualifies for  a successful consumer  creation  Then   set the create - time -  stamp internally to system  time  cns - cre - blo.010.create -  consumer.common.business -  logic.consumer - with - emails - only  PROPOSED   Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a directory 1.0  1.   MCS  E - 330  [SID] :'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 98, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   98  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Chang  e Log  Create a multi PII  consumer with emails  and without mobiles  and   all mandatory fields  are present in the payload  When   identities contains  only emails and is without  mobiles  Then   a new consumer is  created successfully  Support  Flexible  enrollm  ent into  issuer  director  y with  partial  PII  [SID]  cns - cre - blo.011.create -  consumer.common.business -  logic.consumer - with - moblies -  only  PROPOSED  Create a multi PII  consumer with  mobiles and without  emails  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a directory 1.0  and   all mandatory fields  are present in the payload  When   identities contains  only mobiles and is without  emails  Then   a new consumer is  created successfully  1.   MCS  E - 330  [SID] :  Support  Flexible  enrollm  ent into  issuer  director  y with  partial  PII  [SID]  3.5.17.3   SRC Validations  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change  Log  cns - cre - val - 001.create -  consumer.src.validations.residency -  country - code  CURRENT  Reject creation of  consumer in  directory 1.0 without  residency - country -  code  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received for SRC  program  When   consumer  doesn''t have  residency - country -  code  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as  400 bad request  cns - cre - val - 002.create -  consumer.src.validations.preferred -  language.mandatory  CURRENT  Reject creation of  consumer in  directory 1.0 without  preferred - language  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received for SRC  program  When   consumer  doesn''t have  preferred - language  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as  400 bad request'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 99, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   99  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change  Log  cns - cre - val - 003.create -  consumer.src.validations.enrollement -  provider - id  CURRENT  SRC Consumer  must have be  passed with no  enrollment - provider -  id or only ''MA'' as the  possible value  in   enrollment -  provider - id  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received for SRC  program  When   enrollment -  provider - id   is not  absent has any  other value than  ''MA''  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as  400 bad request  cns - cre - val - 004.create -  consumer.src.validations.multi - pii  CURRENT  SRC Consumer  must not have  multiple emails  and/or multiple  mobiles. It must be  created only with  single email and  single mobile.  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received for SRC  program  When   consumer is  having multiple  emails and/or  multiple mobiles  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as  400 bad request  cns - cre - val - 005.create -  consumer.src.validations.root -  email.madatory  CURRENT  Reject SRC  consumer creation  without root - email  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received for SRC  program  When   consumer  doesn''t have root -  email  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as  400 bad request  cns - cre - val - 006.create -  consumer.src.validations.root -  mobile.madatory  CURRENT  Reject SRC  consumer creation  without root - mobile  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received for SRC  program  When   consumer  doesn''t have root -  mobile  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as  400 bad request  3.5.17.4   Companion Validations'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 100, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   100  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  cns - cre - val - 001.create -  consumer.companion.validations.enrollment  - provider - id.mandatory  CURRENT  Reject  creation of  consumer  in directory  1.0 without  enrollment  - provider -  id  Given   a  consumer  creation request  is received for  companion  program  When  consumer  doesn''t have  enrollment -  provider - id  Then   reject the  request and  return the  response as  400 bad request  1.   XID  story  referenc  e  cns - cre - val - 002.create -  consumer.companion.validations.residency -  country - code  CURRENT  Reject  creation of  consumer  in directory  1.0 without  residency -  country -  code  Given   a  consumer  creation request  is received for  companion  program  When   consume  r doesn''t have  residency -  country - code  Then   reject the  request and  return the  response as  400 bad request  1.   XID  story  referenc  e  cns - cre - val - 003.create -  consumer.companion.validations.preferred -  language.mandatory  CURRENT  Reject  creation of  consumer  in directory  1.0 without  preferred -  language  Given   a  consumer  creation request  is received for  companion  program  When   consume  r doesn''t have  preferred -  language  Then   reject the  request and  return the  response as  400 bad request  1.   XID  story  referenc  e  cns - cre - val - 004.create -  consumer.companion.validations.single - pii  CURRENT  Reject  consumer  creation in  companion  program  Given   a  consumer  creation request  is received for  companion  program  1.   XID  story  referenc  e'),
