  ('The_Lighthouse', 154, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   154  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  pgm - cns - cre - def.001.create -  program -  consumer.defaults.marketing - optin  PROPOSED  Treat  marketing - optin  as false by  default  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a  program  When   marketing -  optin consent is not  sent  Then   consider the  default as false and  apply the same  business logic of  false  1.   XID story  reference  3.5.22.3   Conflicts  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  pgm - cns - cre - con.001.create -  program -  consumer.conflicts.directory -  consumer - id  CURRENT  Consumer  request  conflicts  with  existing  consumer  in the  program  Given   a consumer creation  request is received in a program  When   directory - consumer - id  match with existing profile within  the same program - id  Then   return the 409 conflict with  conflict type as  ''DIRECTORY_COSNUMER_ID''.  Include program - consumer  object in the response.  1.   XID story  reference  3.5.22.4   Business Logic  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  pgm - cns - cre -  blo.001.create - program -  consumer.business -  logic.consent - history  CURRENT  Create consent  history record for  acceptance of each of  the consent   -   cookie -  consent - version,  marketing - optin  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a program  When   cookie - consent -  version, marketing -  optin   consents are  accepted  Then   create a consent  history for each of the  consent and  respective version  separately  1.   XID story  reference  pgm - cns - cre -  blo.002.create - program -  consumer.business -  logic.set - create - time  CURRENT  Record create time for  audit purpose  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a program  When   request  qualifies for a  1.   XID story  reference'),
