  ('The_Lighthouse', 158, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   158  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  cns - upd - by - ext - val.003.update -  consumer - by - ext -  id.validations.enrollment -  provider - id.mandatory  CURRENT  enrollment -  provider - id is  mandatory in the  request header  to take the  benefit of  database index  on it during the  consumer  lookup. It is not  meant to  updated but  exists for  technical  optimizations.  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a  directory 1.0  When   request  doesn''t have a  enrollment -  provider - id  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as  400 bad request  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse  cns - upd - by - ext - val.004.update -  consumer - by - ext -  id.validations.identities.duplicates  CURRENT  Consumer  update with  duplicate  identities  (emails/mobiles)  is not allowed  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a  directory 1.0 to  update identities  When   request is  having duplicate  identities  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as  400 bad request  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse  cns - upd - by - ext - val.005.update -  consumer - by - ext -  id.validations.identities.max -  emails  CURRENT  Consumer  update  exceeding the  email limit are  not permitted  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a  directory 1.0 to  update identities  When   number of  emails exceeds the  configurable limit  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as  400 bad request  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse  cns - upd - by - ext - val.006.update -  consumer - by - ext -  id.validations.identities.max -  mobiles  CURRENT  Consumer  exceeding the  mobile limit are  not permitted  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a  directory 1.0 to  update identities  When   number of  ''mobiles phone  numbers''   exceeds  the configurable  limit  Then   reject the  request and return'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 159, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   159  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  the response as  400 bad request  cns - upd - by - ext - val.007.update -  consumer - by - ext -  id.validations.identities.email -  format  CURRENT  Consumer  update having  email address  not in RFC 822  format   -   is not  allowed  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a  directory 1.0 to  update identities  When   email  address is not in  RFC 822 format  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as  400 bad request  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse  cns - upd - by - ext - val.008.update -  consumer - by - ext -  id.validations.identities.mobile -  format  CURRENT  Consumer  update with  mobile number  which doesn''t  comply with  given regex  Given   a consumer  creation request is  received in a  directory 1.0 to  update identities  When   mobile  number doesn''t  comply with   Regex  -   "^[0 - 9]{4,14}$"  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as  400 bad request  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse  cns - upd - by - ext - val.009.update -  consumer - by - ext -  id.validations.identities.mobile -  country - code - format  CURRENT  Consumer with  mobile country  code which  doesn''t comply  with given regex  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a  directory 1.0  When   mobile  country code  doesn''t comply  with   Regex  -   "^[+]?[0 - 9]{1,4}$"  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as  400 bad request  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse  cns - upd - by - ext - val.010.update -  consumer - by - ext -  id.validations.national - id  CURRENT  Update to  National Id is not  allowed   if  disabled in  region - config -  library  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a  directory 1.0 to  update national id  When   national id is  configured as not  editable in region  config library (for  the consumer''s  residency country