  ('The_Lighthouse', 160, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   160  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  code either coming  from request or  from database   -   if  not coming from  request)  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as  400 bad request  cns - upd - by - ext - val.011.update -  consumer - by - ext -  id.validations.national - id  CURRENT  National Id of the  consumer needs  to comply with  validations of  region -   config -  library  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a  directory 1.0 to  update national id  When   national id is  configured as  updatable in region  config library but it  doesn''t comply  with other  configurations  available in region  config library   (for  the consumer''s  residency country  code either coming  from request or  from database (in  case if not coming  from request))  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as  400 bad request  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse  cns - upd - by - ext - val.012.update -  consumer - by - ext -  id.validations.preferred - email  CURRENT  Consumer  update in a  directory can be  with at least one  and at max one  preferred email  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a  directory 1.0 with  emails  When   no preferred  email or more than  preferred emails  are received  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as  400 bad request  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse  cns - upd - by - ext - val.013.update -  consumer - by - ext -  id.validations.preferred - mobile  CURRENT  Consumer  update in a  directory can be  with at least one  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a  directory 1.0 with  mobiles  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 161, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   161  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  and at max one  preferred mobile  When   no preferred  mobile or more  than preferred  mobiles are  received  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as  400 bad request  3.5.23.2   Defaults  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  3.5.23.3   Conflicts  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  cns - upd - by - ext -  con.001.update - consumer -  by - ext - id.conflicts.identities  CURRENT  Consumer update  with identities  conflicts with any  other profile  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a  directory 1.0 to  update identities  When   identities  (some/all) match  with any other profile  within the same  program id  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as 400  bad request  1.   First version  under project  Lighthouse  3.5.23.4   Business Logic  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  cns - upd - by - ext -  blo.001.update -  consumer - by -  ext - id.business -  logic.identities  CURRENT  Update to the identities is  a replace operation   -   It  will replace all existing  identities with the new  identities from request  Given   the request is  received in a directory 1.0  to update the identities of  consumer  When   all mandatory fields  are present in the payload  and new identities don''t  conflict with any other  consumer (within the same  program - id) based on  conflict rules  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 162, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   162  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  Then   existing identities of  the consumer in database  are replaced with new  identities from the request  successfully  cns - upd - by - ext -  blo.002.update -  consumer - by -  ext - id.business -  logic.identities  CURRENT  Swagger should  automatically pick the  value object inside the  identities array based on  selected type field.  If type is EMAIL, then  email object should  automatically be picked  for value.  If type is MOBILE, mobile  object should  automatically be picked  for value.  Given   a consumer update  request is received in a  directory 1.0  When   identities are  present  Then   even before  processing the request,  swagger should  automatically pick the value  object inside the identities  array based on selected  type field   -   If type is EMAIL,  email object should  automatically be picked for  value.  If type is MOBILE, mobile  object should automatically  be picked for value.  Reject the request if  mismatches found.  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse  cns - upd - by - ext -  blo.003.update -  consumer - by -  ext - id.business -  logic.pii - data -  storage  CURRENT  All PII data of the  consumer should be  stored only in encrypted  and masked format in the  database. PII data should  not be stored in plain text.  Given   a consumer update  request is received in a  directory 1.0 to update PII  data  When   PII data is present  Then   PII data is stored only  in encrypted and masked  format in the database  without storing in the plain  text  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse  cns - upd - by - ext -  blo.004.update -  consumer - by -  ext - id.business -  logic.consent -  history  CURRENT  Create consent history  record for updates to  acceptance of each of the  consent   -   tnc_version,  privacy_policy_version,  cookie_consent_version  and marketing_optin  Given   a consumer update  request is received in a  directory 1.0 to update  consents  When   tnc_version,  privacy_policy_version,  cookie_consent_version  and  marketing_optin   consents  are updated  Then   create a consent  history for each of the  consent and respective  version separately by  preserving the previous  consent history  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 163, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   163  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  cns - upd - by - ext -  blo.005.update -  consumer - by -  ext - id.business -  logic.consumer -  with - emails - only  CURRENT  Update consumer with  emails and without  mobiles is NOT allowed  Given   a consumer update  request is received in a  directory 1.0 and   all  mandatory fields are  present in the payload  When   request contains only  emails and is without  mobiles  Then   reject the request and  return the response as 400  bad request  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse  PROPOSED  Update consumer with  emails and without  mobiles is allowed  Given   a consumer update  request is received in a  directory 1.0 and   all  mandatory fields are  present in the payload  When   request contains only  emails and is without  mobiles  Then   a consumer is  updated successfully by  replacing the existing  identities with new identities  coming from the request.  1.   MCSE - 330 [SID]  : Support Flexible  enrollment into  issuer directory with  partial PII [SID]  cns - upd - by - ext -  blo.006.update -  consumer - by -  ext - id.business -  logic.consumer -  with - mobiles -  only  CURRENT  Update consumer with  mobiles and without  emails is NOT allowed  Given   a consumer update  request is received in a  directory 1.0 and   all  mandatory fields are  present in the payload  When   request contains only  mobiles and is without  emails  Then   reject the request and  return the response as 400  bad request  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse  PROPOSED  Update consumer with  mobiles and without  emails is allowed  Given   a consumer update  request is received in a  directory and   all mandatory  fields are present in the  payload  When   request contains only  mobiles and is without  emails  Then   a consumer is  updated successfully by  replacing the existing  identities with new identities  coming from the request.  1.   MCSE - 330 [SID]  : Support Flexible  enrollment into  issuer directory with  partial PII [SID]'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 164, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   164  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  cns - upd - by - ext -  blo.007.update -  consumer - by -  ext - id.business -  logic.litigation -  hold  CURRENT  Don''t allow the updates to  a consumer held up for  litigation  Given   a consumer update  request is received in a  directory 1.0  When   the consumer is held  up for litigation  Then   reject the update to a  consumer in directory  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse  cns - upd - by - ext -  blo.008.update -  consumer - by -  ext - id.business -  logic.unlock  CURRENT  Unlock a consumer  record  Given   a consumer update  request is received in a  directory 1.0  When   consumer record is  locked and lock expiration  time has elapsed  Then   account is unlocked  while updating the  consumer  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse  cns - upd - by - ext -  blo.009.update -  consumer - by -  ext - id.business -  logic.dont -  unlock  CURRENT  Don''t unlock a consumer  Given   a consumer update  request is received in a  directory 1.0  When   consumer record is  locked and lock expiration  time has not elapsed  Then   update the consumer  without unlocking the  account  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse  cns - upd - by - ext -  blo.010.update -  consumer - by -  ext - id.business -  logic.non -  existent - account  CURRENT  Attempt to update a non  existent consumer  Given   a consumer update  request is received in a  directory 1.0  When   a  matching   consumer record  is not found within a  program id  Then   return the 404 NOT  FOUND response  1.   First  version  under  project  Lighthouse  cns - upd - by - ext -  blo.011.update -  consumer - by -  ext - id.business -  logic.set - last -  update - time  CURRENT  Record update time for  audit purpose  Given   a consumer update  request is received in a  directory 1.0  When   request qualifies for  a successful update  Then   set the last - up