  ('The_Lighthouse', 174, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   174  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  one preferred  email  When   no  preferred email  or more than  preferred emails  are received  Then   reject the  request and  return the  response as 400  bad request  dir - cns - upd - val.017.update - directory -  consumer.validations.preferred - mobile  PROPOSED  Consumer  update in a  directory can  be with at least  one and at max  one preferred  mobile  Given   a  consumer  update request is  received in a  directory with  mobiles  When   no  preferred mobile  or more than  preferred  mobiles are  received  Then   reject the  request and  return the  response as 400  bad request  1.   XID  story  referenc  e  3.5.24.2   Defaults  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  dir - cns - upd - def.001.update - directory -  consumer.defaults.parameters.type  PROPOSED  Consumer will  be updated  using  directory -  consumer - id  by default  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a  directory  When   '' type''  parameter is not  specified in  request  Then   consumer  will be updated  using directory -  consumer - id by  default  1.   XID story  reference  3.5.24.3   Conflicts'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 175, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   175  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  dir - cns - upd - con.001.update -  directory -  consumer.conflicts.identities  PROPOSED  Consumer update  with identities  conflicts with any  other profile  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a  directory to update  identities  When   identities  (some/all) match  with any other  profile within the  same directory  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as  400 bad request  1.   XID story  reference  3.5.24.4   Business Logic   -   UPDATE AS A REPLACE  An update operation replaces existing data. The update process requires the client to first  retrieve the resource, then send the full request body with any updated fields. Only the changed  values are replaced in the database; unchanged values remain as the y were. If a required field  is missing from the request, it will be rejected. Optional fields that are not included in the request  will have their existing values set to null in the database. Identities and consents once provided,  can be updated but cannot   be removed or set to null in the Update operation.  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  dir - cns - upd -  blo.001.update -  directory -  consumer.business -  logic.replace  PROPOSED  Update is a replace  operation.  Given   the request is  received in a  directory to update  the consumer  When   all mandatory  fields are present in  the payload and  new identities don''t  conflict with any  other consumer  based on conflict  rules  Then   existing  attributes of the  consumer in  database are  replaced with new  values from the  request successfully  1.   XID  story  referenc  e  dir - cns - upd -  blo.002.update -  directory -  consumer.business -  logic.empty - request  PROPOSED  Empty request body is  rejected.  Given   the request is  received in a  directory to update  the consumer  When   request body  is empty  1.   XID  story  referenc  e'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 176, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   176  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  Then   reject the  request and return  the response as 400  bad request  dir - cns - upd -  blo.003.update -  directory -  consumer.business -  logic.valid - update  PROPOSED  Update only changed  values.  Given   the request is  received in a  directory to update  the consumer  When   all mandatory  fields are present  and valid in the  payload and new  identities don''t  conflict with any  other consumer  based on conflict  rules  Then   only the  changed values are  replaced in the  database and  unchanged values  remain as they  were. Apply  respective field level  validations only to  those fields where  value has changed.  Don''t apply field  level validations to  those fields where  value is  unchanged, so  that request  doesn''t result in  unnecessary  rejection.  For example   -  validation on  National - Id etc.  1.   XID  story  referenc  e  dir - cns - upd -  blo.004.update -  directory -  consumer.business -  logic.first - name  PROPOSED  First name not available in  the request  Given   a request is  received in a  directory to update  the consumer  When   the request is  without first - name  Then   set the first -  name as null for  consumer record in  a database  1.   XID  story  referenc  e  dir - cns - upd -  blo.005.update -  directory -  PROPOSED   Given   a request is  received in a  1.   XID  story'),
