  ('The_Lighthouse', 193, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   193  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  record this instance of  ignoring update to the  marketing - opt - out - time  pgm - cns - upd -  blo.014.update - program -  consumer.business -  logic.marketing - opt - out -  time  PROPOSED  new marketing - opt - out -  time should be greater  than existing marketing -  opt - in - time  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a program  to update marketing -  opt - out - time  When   marketing - opt -  out - time from the  request is less than  marketing - opt - in - time of  the consumer record in  database  Then   ignore the update  to marketing - opt - out -  time and continue with  processing updates of  other attributes. Also  add the warning log to  record this instance of  ignoring update to the  marketing - opt - out - time  1.   XID story  referenc  e  pgm - cns - upd -  blo.015.update - program -  consumer.business -  logic.marketing - opt - in -  to - marketing - opt - out  PROPOSED  Consumer who  previously opted - in for  marketing  communication wants to  opt out now  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a program  to opt out of marketing  When   consumer was  previously opted - in  Then   consumer should  be opted out usefully by  setting opt out fields  1.   XID story  referenc  e  pgm - cns - upd -  blo.016.update - program -  consumer.business -  logic.marketing - opt - out -  to - marketing - opt - in  PROPOSED  Consumer who  previously opted - out of  marketing  communication   -   wants  to opt in now  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a program  to opt in for marketing  When   consumer was  previously opted - out  Then   consumer should  be opted in usefully by  setting opt in fields  1.   XID story  referenc  e  pgm - cns - upd -  blo.017.update - program -  consumer.business -  logic.consent - history  PROPOSED  Create consent history  record for updates to  acceptance of each of  the consent   -  cookie_consent_version  , marketing_optin  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a program  to update consents  When  cookie_consent_versio  n and/or  marketing_optin  consents are updated  1.   XID story  referenc  e'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 194, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   194  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  Then   create a consent  history for each of the  consent and respective  version separately by  preserving the previous  consent history  pgm - cns - upd -  blo.018.update - program -  consumer.business -  logic.update - with -  program - consumer - id  PROPOSED  Update a consumer with  program - consumer - id  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a program  When   request is sent  using program -  consumer - id  Then   search and  update a consumer  record using program -  consumer - id only (and  not using directory -  consumer - id)  1.   XID story  referenc  e  pgm - cns - upd -  blo.019.update - program -  consumer.business -  logic.update - with -  directory - consumer - id  PROPOSED  Update a consumer with  directory - consumer - id  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a program  When   request is sent  using directory -  consumer - id  Then   search and  update a consumer  record using directory -  consumer - id only (and  not using program -  consumer - id)  1.   XID story  referenc  e  pgm - cns - upd -  blo.020.update - program -  consumer.business -  logic.non - existent -  account  PROPOSED  Attempt to update a non  existent consumer  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a program  When   a  matching   consumer  record is not found in a  program  Then   return the 404  NOT FOUND response  1.   XID story  referenc  e  pgm - cns - upd -  blo.021.update - program -  consumer.business -  logic.set - update - time  PROPOSED  Record update time for  audit purpose  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a program  When   request qualifies  for a successful update  Then   set the update -  time internally to  system time  1.   XID story  referenc  e'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 195, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   195  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  pgm - cns - upd -  blo.022.update - program -  consumer.business -  logic.last - used - time  PROPOSED  Validate last_used_time  of consumer  Note   -   A 1000 ms (1  second) buffer is  needed because the  Checkout Service clock  runs about 25 ms ahead  of the Consumer  Service, causing update  requests to be rejected  over tiny timing  differences. This buffer  ensures that only  significant time  mismatches a re flagged,  while routine updates  proceed smoothly.  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a program  to update  last_used_time  When  1) last_used_time   is  greater than 1000 ms  from now() in the future  OR  2) If last_used_time   is  in the past more than a  day from now()  Then   reject the request  and return the response  as 400 bad request  1.   XID story  referenc  e  pgm - cns - upd -  blo.023.update - program -  consumer.business -  logic.last - checkout - time  PROPOSED  Validate  last_checkout_time of  consumer  Note   -   A 1000 ms (1  second) buffer is  needed because the  Checkout Service clock  runs about 25 ms ahead  of the Consumer  Service, causing update  requests to be rejected  over tiny timing  differences. This buffer  ensures that only  significant time  mismatches a re flagged,  while routine updates  proceed smoothly.  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a program  to update  last_checkout_time  When  1) If  last_checkout_time   is  greater than 1000 ms  from now() in the future  OR  2) If  last_checkout_time   is in  the past more than a  day from now() OR  3) If last_checkout_time  is past the  last_checkout_time of  existing consumer  Then   reject the request  and return the response  as 400 bad request  1.   XID story  referenc  e  pgm - cns - upd -  blo.024.update - program -  consumer.business -  logic.typical - flow  PROPOSED  create directory  consumer → create  program - consumer →  get the program  consumer → update  program consumer  using the same values  from the response of get  call  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a program  When  the below mentioned  flow is being followed  1) Create Directory  Consumer  2) Create Program  Consumer  1.   XID story  referenc  e'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 196, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   196  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  3) Get Program  Consumer  4) Update program  consumer using the  same values from the  response of get call  Then   process the  update request  successfully   based on  business rules  pgm - cns - upd -  blo.025.update - program -  consumer.business -  logic.typical - flow  PROPOSED  create directory  consumer → create  program - consumer →  again try to create the  same program  consumer so that we get  the conflict → update  program consumer  using the same values  from the response of the  conflict  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a program  When  the below mentioned  flow is being followed  1) Create Directory  Consumer  2) Create Program  Consumer  3) Again try to create  the same program  consumer so that we  get the conflict  4) Update program  consumer using the  same values from the  response of the conflict  Then   process the  update request  successfully based on  business rules  1.   XID story  referenc  e  3.5.25.5   KPI Events  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  pgm - cns - upd -  kpi.001.update - program -  consumer.kpi.started  PROPOSED  Update program  consumer request  will publish the KPI  event for  ''STARTED''  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a program  When   request is  processed  Then   publish the KPI  event for STARTED  state before starting  any processing to  record the start of the  request   -   Directory 2.0  KPI events  1.   XID story  reference'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 197, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   197  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  pgm - cns - upd -  kpi.002.update - program -  consumer.kpi.failed  PROPOSED  Update program  consumer request  will publish the KPI  event for ''FAILED''  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a program  When   request gets  failed  Then   publish the KPI  event for FAILED to  record failure of the  request   -   Directory 2.0  KPI events  1.   XID story  reference  pgm - cns - upd -  kpi.003.update - program -  consumer.kpi.completed  PROPOSED  Update program  consumer request  will publish the KPI  event for  ''COMPLETED''  Given   a consumer  update request is  received in a program  When   request gets  completed  Then   publish the KPI  event for COMPLETED  to record completion of  the request   -   Directory  2.0 KPI events  1.   XID story  reference  3.5.25.6   Successful Requests  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  3.5.26   Consumer service : Data Model and Entity overview  3.5.26.1   Consumer 1.0  3.5.26.2'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 198, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   198  Consumer Multi PII   -   Use Case  3.5.26.3   Consumer 2.0 (Directory or Program Consumer)'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 199, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   199  3.5.26.4   Consumer 2.0 (Program Consumer)'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 200, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   200  3.5.26.5   Entity overview <Sample from O&R   Deepak Gite   to update>  •   Company:   Root entity in MACS onboarding domain. It is the Mastercard''s client''s  information in system as per onboarding done under Franchise process. Key attributes  are CID, legal name.  •   SRC client / SRC project:   also known as SRCI (SRC Initiator). It is the entity created  under company which is used to create the client''s profile for onboarding to MCS  platform for using program capabilities. One or more SRC clients (a.k.a SRC projects)  can be created to have sepa rate configurations added as per client needs.  •   Key:   Keys are attached to SRC client; to be uploaded by client user for interacting with  system.  o   Signing keys: One or more Public keys uploaded by client for performing OAuth  while calling b2b apis over APIGW (ex. DPA registration api)  o   Encryption keys: Public key(s) uploaded by client for payload encryption  purpose (consumed by core checkout services for fulfilling the checkout  request). Max 3 allowed currently; one by default in use at a time.  •   Merchant:   Clients of SRCIs participating in checkout, which get onboarded via PCI  compliant SRCIs to MACS platform. Under MCS onboarding domain, the terms  merchants and DPAs are same entities.  •   Program Type:   Key offerings (checkout types) provided by MACS platform to its  clients. SRCIs to upload the DPAs (Digital Payment Application) under one or more  program types (depend on eligibility). Ex. Click 2 Pay, Card On File.  •   Program instance:   An instance of program type associated with specific entity (SRCI /  DPA) based on type of program. Key attributes are program id (a.k.a service id),  program name (a.k.a. CFEN: Consumer Facing Entity Name), TRID (Token Requestor  Id).  3.5.27   Consumer Service : ER Diagram  3.5.27.1   Prod Environment  3.5.27.2   Stage Environment'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 201, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   201  3.5.28   Consumer Service API Sequence Diagrams  This page contains detailed sequence diagrams for all API endpoints exposed by the Consumer  Service application. Each diagram shows the complete flow from client request through all  service layers to the database and back.  Last Updated:   February 19, 2026  Total Endpoints:   16  Diagrams Location:   consumer -  service/documents/designs/sequence_diagrams/  3.5.28.1   Table of Contents  •   Consumer Service API Sequence Diagrams  o   Table of Contents  o   Summary Table  o   Consumer Controller Endpoints  ▪   1. Create Consumer  ▪   2. Get Consumer By ID  ▪   3. Update Consumer By ID  ▪   4. Delete Consumer By ID  ▪   5. Update Consumer Status  ▪   6. Get Consumer By External Consumer ID  ▪   7. Update Consumer By External Consumer ID  ▪   8. Delete Consumer By External Consumer ID  ▪   9. Search Consumers  ▪   10. Searches Consumers (Multi - Criteria)  ▪   11. Consent History Search  o   Verification Controller Endpoints  ▪   12. Record External Verification  ▪   13. Get Verification By ID  ▪   14. Delete Verification (Delete OTP)  ▪   15. Get Verification Channels By Consumer ID'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 202, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   202  3.5.28.2   Summary Table  Endpoint   Method   Description   Controller  /consumers   POST   Create new  consumer  ConsumerController  /consumers/{consumer - id}   GET   Get  consumer by  ID  ConsumerController  /consumers/{consumer - id}   PUT   Update  consumer by  ID  ConsumerController  /consumers/{consumer - id}   DELETE   Delete  consumer by  ID  ConsumerController  /consumers/{consumer -  id}/updateStatus  POST   Update  consumer  status  ConsumerController  /consumers/external - id/{external -  consumer - id}  GET   Get  consumer by  external ID  ConsumerController  /consumers/external - id/{external -  consumer - id}  PUT   Update  consumer by  external ID  ConsumerController  /consumers/external - id/{external -  consumer - id}  DELETE   Delete  consumer by  external ID  ConsumerController  /consumers/search   GET/POS  T  Search  consumers  (dynamic  criteria)  ConsumerController  /consumers/searches   POST   Search  consumers  (multi -  criteria)  ConsumerController  /consumers/consentHistory/search   POST   Search  consent  history  ConsentHistoryControll  er  /verifications/record   POST   Record  external  verification  VerificationController  /verifications/{verification - id}   GET   Get  verification  by ID  VerificationController  /verifications/{verification - id}   DELETE   Delete/canc  el  verification  VerificationController  /verifications/consumers/{consume  r - id}  GET   Get  verification  channels  VerificationController'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 203, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   203  3.5.28.3   Consumer Controller Endpoints  3.5.28.3.1   1. Create Consumer  Endpoint:   POST   /consumers  Description:   Creates a new consumer with the provided details. Supports both standard and  Multi - PII consumer creation.  View Sequence Diagram   -   Create Consumer  3.5.28.3.2   2. Get Consumer By ID  Endpoint:   GET   /consumers/{consumer - id}  Description:   Fetches consumer by UUID. Returns masked or unmasked PII based on the  request parameter.  View Sequence Diagram   -   Get Consumer By ID'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 204, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   204  3.5.28.3.3   3. Update Consumer By ID  Endpoint:   PUT   /consumers/{consumer - id}  Description:   Updates existing consumer by ID. Validates mobile conflicts and handles PII  encryption.  View Sequence Diagram   -   Update Consumer By ID'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 205, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   205  3.5.28.3.4   4. Delete Consumer By ID  Endpoint:   DELETE   /consumers/{consumer - id}  Description:   Deletes consumer and all related records (consent history, throttles, verifications).  View Sequence Diagram   -   Delete Consumer By ID'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 206, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   206  3.5.28.3.5   5. Update Consumer Status  Endpoint:   POST   /consumers/{consumer - id}/updateStatus  Description:   Updates consumer status to ACTIVE or LOCKED. Clears throttle records on  status change.  View Sequence Diagram   -   Update Consumer Status  3.5.28.3.6   6. Get Consumer By External Consumer ID  Endpoint:   GET   /consumers/external - id/{external - consumer - id}  Description:   Fetches consumer by external consumer ID and enrollment provider ID (Multi - PII  feature).'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 207, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   207  View Sequence Diagram   -   Get Consumer By External ID  3.5.28.3.7   7. Update Consumer By External Consumer ID  Endpoint:   PUT   /consumers/external - id/{external - consumer - id}  Description:   Updates consumer by external consumer ID. Handles Multi - PII identity updates.  View Sequence Diagram   -   Update Consumer By External ID  3.5.28.3.8   8. Delete Consumer By External Consumer ID  Endpoint:   DELETE   /consumers/external - id/{external - consumer - id}  Description:   Deletes consumer by external consumer ID and enrollment provider ID.  View Sequence Diagram   -   Delete Consumer By External ID'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 208, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   208  3.5.28.3.9   9. Search Consumers  Endpoint:   GET/POST   /consumers/search  Description:   Searches consumers using dynamic criteria with ANTLR parsing. Supports  firstName, lastName, email, mobile, and other fields.  View Sequence Diagram   -   Search Consumers  3.5.28.3.10   10. Searches Consumers (Multi - Criteria)  Endpoint:   POST   /consumers/searches  Description:   Searches consumers using structured criteria types: SEARCH_BY_ID,  SEARCH_BY_EMAIL, SEARCH_BY_MOBILE, SEARCH_BY_EXTERNAL_ACCOUNT_ID, etc.  View Sequence Diagram   -   Searches Consumers (Multi - Criteria)'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 209, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   209  3.5.28.3.11   11. Consent History Search  Endpoint:   POST   /consumers/consentHistory/search  Description:   Searches consumer consent history by consumerId, email, or mobile. Joins with  consent document records.  View Sequence Diagram   -   Consent History Search'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 210, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   210  3.5.28.4   Verification Controller Endpoints  3.5.28.4.1   12. Record External Verification  Endpoint:   POST   /verifications/record  Description:   Records externally validated verification. Handles SUCCESS/FAILURE status and  account locking logic.  View Sequence Diagram   -   Record External Verification'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 211, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   211  3.5.28.4.2   13. Get Verification By ID  Endpoint:   GET   /verifications/{verification - id}  Description:   Gets verification record by ID. Returns attempts left and verification status.  View Sequence Diagram   -   Get Verification By ID'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 212, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   212  3.5.28.4.3   14. Delete Verification (Delete OTP)  Endpoint:   DELETE   /verifications/{verification - id}  Description:   Cancels a verification/OTP by setting status to CANCELLED.  View Sequence Diagram   -   Delete Verification'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 213, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   213  3.5.28.4.4   15. Get Verification Channels By Consumer ID  Endpoint:   GET   /verifications/consumers/{consumer - id}  Description:   Gets verified verification channels (EMAIL, SMS) for a consumer.  View Sequence Diagram   -   Get Verification Channels'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 214, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   214  Note:   All sequence diagrams are also available as PlantUML source files in the  repository at   consumer - service/documents/designs/sequence_diagrams/  3.5.29   Consumer Service Tech Debt Tracker  Sr.  No.  Title   Description   Priority  1   Plain text PII data in  external_account_id  Previously, the profile service incorrectly sent consumers''  email addresses in the external_account field to the  consumer service for companion programs (when  Identity_Type was EMAIL). As this field was not designed  for PII, it stored these emails in plain   text. The profile  service fixed the defect on their side and now sends a null  value when Identity_Type is EMAIL, but existing plain text  data remains in the consumer domain and needs a  remediation.  High  3.5.30  •   consumer.search.1  •   consumer.search.2  •   consumer.search.3  Behavior ID   Title   Behavior   Change Log  feature/Story  Reference  consumer.search.1   SearchByEmail -   verify  200 ok status code when  searching consumer for a  valid email /exact match  with multiple programIds.  GIVEN that consumer is  already created and  exists in the database,  WHEN the post search  API is called with valid  header information AND  a valid email exact  match in request body,  THEN the consumer  data object should be  returned with a 200 ok  Initial version  Initial support has  been introduced  as a part of  AgentPay  <reference to  feature>  consumer.search.2'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 215, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   215  Behavior ID   Title   Behavior   Change Log  feature/Story  Reference  consumer.search.3   Given   that checkout  service <End point> has  called with evidence of  authentication  When   cloud token and  DSRP based is  concluded for checkout  payload  Then  1) authentication status  has been appropriately  downgraded or  maintained following  principle and matrix   -   < -  --- >  2) for   authenticated  transaction appropriate  indicators to be sent to  DTS for authorization  message enrichment  3.6   DCF Service Dashboard  3.6.1   Table of Contents  •   Overview  •   Dependencies  •   Endpoints & behavior  o   Swagger   -  •   Service Capabilities and configurations  •   High - Level Interaction Diagrams  •   Current Performance Metrics  •   Technical Roadmap  •   Technical Infrastructure  •   Team and ALM  3.6.2   Overview  •   Description:'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 216, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   216  DCF (Digital Card Facilitator) is a crucial front end UI within Mastercard Click to Pay (C2P)  that provides   consumer with access to the selected digital card, interface to review and  confirm the transaction / consumer details and facilitate the payment confirmation  o   DCF hosts a robust interface to display selected card details and captures  consumer details such as   name, billing address, shipping address and any  further PII information related to the transaction initiated by the merchants  o   Performs cardholder authentication (e.g. OTP when a known user checks out  on an unknown device), ensuring a secure checkout experience.  o   Presents relevant Terms and Conditions and collects relevant consumer  consent  •   Purpose & Scope:  o   DCF serves to upstream services by communicating with various downstream  services. The ultimate purpose is providing merchants/integrators and their  consumers a secure and easy checkout process (for both B2B and B2C) by  ▪   being launched through the DCF URL through checkout method,  directly invoked using the DCF URL by B2B merchants  ▪   providing a secure front end interface to perform consumer  authentication  ▪   Calling /bind API to perform the below functionalities  •   provision the profile  •   bind the card to existing profile  •   update collected missing consumer information  •   update latest Terms & Conditions for the profile  o   Recognized devices, MRT Tokens, Passkeys?  o   Third Party JWT?  •   DCF Checkout Flows  o  ▪   First - Time User Enrollment  •   Consumer enters card details and personal info.  •   DCF captures data, enrolls them into Click to Pay.  •   Loads the digital card inside Checkout UI for use.  ▪   Recognized User on a New Device  •   User inputs email/mobile.  •   DCF triggers identity lookup; detects a registered profile.  •   DCF sends OTP, validates; collects consent.  •   Presents the digital card for transaction confirmation  ▪   Returning User on a Recognized Device  •   Skip OTP: user simply selects the stored card and completes  the checkout.'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 217, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   217  3.6.3   Dependencies  This table lists and describes all services or systems that provide input or trigger events for this  microservice or rely on data or functionalities from this microservice.  Service Name   Type   Service Dashboard  Pre - Checkout   Downstream   Pre - Checkout Service Dashboard  MCS SDK   Downstream  UCS (SRCi - SDK)   Upstream  B2B Integrator   Upstream  TCS/bind   Downstream  PI Core   Downstream  Consumer Service   Downstream   Consumer Service Dashboard  CaaS   Downstream  Address Service   Downstream  CDS   Downstream  Authentication   Downstream  DPA Registration Service (Post MOD)   Downstream  Checkout   Downstream   Checkout Service Dashboard  Bulk Service   Downstream  appInstanceService   Downstream  benefitService   Downstream  3.6.4   Endpoints & behavior  3.6.4.1   Swagger   -  This table lists all endpoints that''s utilized by DCF along with a brief description.  Endpoint   Purpose/F  unctionali  ty  Endpoint Level Use  Cases/Scenarios  KP  I  Ev  ent  s  Seq  uen  ce  Diag  ram  Downs  tream(  s)  A  v  g  T  P  S  P  ea  k  T  P  S  Proj  ecte  d  TPS  Avg  Res  pon  se  Tim  e  P90  Res  pon  se  Tim  e  /bind   •   pr  ovi  sio  n  the  https://sandbox.src.mastercar  d.com/api/bind'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 218, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   218  Endpoint   Purpose/F  unctionali  ty  Endpoint Level Use  Cases/Scenarios  KP  I  Ev  ent  s  Seq  uen  ce  Diag  ram  Downs  tream(  s)  A  v  g  T  P  S  P  ea  k  T  P  S  Proj  ecte  d  TPS  Avg  Res  pon  se  Tim  e  P90  Res  pon  se  Tim  e  pr  ofil  e  •   bin  d  the  car  d  to  exi  sti  ng  pr  ofil  e  •   up  dat  e  col  lec  ted  mi  ssi  ng  co  ns  um  er  inf  or  ma  tio  n  •   up  dat  e  lat  est  Te  rm  s  &  Co  ndi  tio  ns  for  the  pr  ofil  e'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 219, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   219  Endpoint   Purpose/F  unctionali  ty  Endpoint Level Use  Cases/Scenarios  KP  I  Ev  ent  s  Seq  uen  ce  Diag  ram  Downs  tream(  s)  A  v  g  T  P  S  P  ea  k  T  P  S  Proj  ecte  d  TPS  Avg  Res  pon  se  Tim  e  P90  Res  pon  se  Tim  e  /transactio  nCredenti  als  Called at  checkout  to finialize  the  transaction  before  sending  the  payload  back to the  user  https://sandbox.src.mastercar  d.com/api/transactionCredent  ials  /verificatio  n  •   aut  he  nti  cat  ion  ste  p  up  /validation   •   cal  led  aft  er  the  OT  P  ent  er  ed  by  the  us  er'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 220, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   220  3.6.5   Service Capabilities and configurations  Service capabilities can be accessed through   Auto Enrollment Configuration for Issuers   -  SRC Checkout Product Strategy   -   Confluence  Do we need separate one for C2P?  3.6.6   High - Level Interaction Diagrams  •   Sequence Diagrams:  •   ER Diagram :  •   Component interaction   -  •   Data Model:  3.6.7   Current Performance Metrics  •   Metrics:  Consumer Service Production Statistics .  •   Monitoring:  o   Link to Dynatrace dashboards   -  ▪   Global   -   Consumer Service Insights  ▪   Pune   -   Consumer Service https://sft042.dynatrace -  managed.com/e/95d25318 - 8269 - 4c27 - a2e3 -  e83f8a22c4ab/#dashboard;gtf=yesterday;gf=all;id=28eb163e - 05b2 -  4c74 - 8c2d - 43ce70e0c63b;applyDashboardDefaults=true Insights  ▪   MACS Service Availability  o   SRE Alerts  ▪   Consumer Service Alerts  3.6.8   Technical Roadmap  •   Atlas Tech Debt Tracker   -   Alberta   -   Confluence  •   Checkout Service technical roadmap  3.6.9   Technical Infrastructure  Name   Link  Techni  cal  Asset  Details  https://sso.internal.eportal.mastercard.int/pgmctg - prod - portal/program - catalog -  ui/#/technical - assets/5500/details   Replace  Reposit  ory  https://scm.mastercard.int/stash/projects/ALBERTA/repos/consumer - service/browse  Replace  Postma  n  Collecti  on  https://scm.mastercard.int/stash/projects/ALBERTA/repos/postman -  tests/browse/consumer - service/Consumer - Service.postman_collection.json   Replace'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 221, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   221  Name   Link  Oracle  Databa  se  https://confluence.mastercard.int/pages/viewpage.action?spaceKey=alberta&title=Atla  s+Onboarding#AtlasOnboarding - OracleDatabaseAccess   Replace  Secure  d  Access  Policy  https://scm.mastercard.int/stash/projects/SPMADMIN/repos/com - mastercard - digital -  platform_consumer - services/browse   Replace  Static  Code  Analysi  s Tool  https://fusion.mastercard.int/sonar/dashboard?branch=dev&id=com.mastercard%3Aco  nsumer - service   Replace  Black  Duck  Scan  https://mc.app.blackduck.com/api/search/project -  versions?limit=100&offset=0&q=consumer%20service   Replace  3.6.10   Team and ALM  •   Team:  Mastercard Checkout Services   -   Team Composition  •   ALM Current Iteration Status:  Hercules Iteration Board   - Replace with JIRA  •   Prod Support Escalation:  Hercules Escalation   -   Alberta   -   Confluence  •   Iteration Planning Board:  Atlas (Consumer and Installments) › Iteration Planning | Rally   Replace with JIRA  •   Team ALM Board:  Atlas (Consumer and Installments) › Team Board | Rally   Replace with JIRA  •   Open Defects:  Atlas Owned Defects   Replace with JIRA  3.7   Directory Orchestrator Service Dashboard  3.7.1   Table of Contents  •   Overview  •   Dependencies  •   Endpoints & behavior  o   Endpoints Overview  o   Directory 2.0 : Directory Consumer Endpoints  o   Directory 2.0 : Program Consumer Endpoints  o   Directory 2.0 : Consumer Manager Endpoints  •   High - Level Design Artifacts  •   Operational and Performance references  •   Technical Roadmap'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 222, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   222  •   Technical Infrastructure  •   Team and ALM  3.7.2   Overview  •   Description:  Directory Orchestrator Service is a program - agnostic platform service within the MACS that  manages consumer profiles from creation to deletion. It oversees consumer verification,  which will transition to the authentication service, and handles consent mana gement,  keeping records of all consents given by consumers.  •   Purpose & Scope:  o   As an orchestrator service, it delivers significant business value to MACS by  supporting various flows such as B2C (Click To Pay) and B2B (SCOF).  o   It also offers separate directories for each issuer, enhancing trust and  compliance. This allows issuers to securely onboard consumer data and  enables MACS to provide auto - enrolment solutions where issuers remain in  control of their data.  o   Additionally, the MACS supports third - party wallets (e.g. Samsung) by allowing  wallets to provision consumer and wallet information in the directory. This  enables the presentation of wallet credentials during a payment experience and  facilitates seamless l inking or redirection to the Wallet interface when a  consumer selects a wallet for payment.  3.7.3   Dependencies  This table lists and describes all services or systems that provide input or trigger events for this  microservice or rely on data or functionalities from this microservice.  Service Name   Type   Service Dashboard  Bulk Provisioning   Upstream  Program Activation Service   Downstream  Profile   Downstream  TCS   Downstream  Checkout   Upstream  Consumer Scheduler   Upstream  CaaS   Downstream  High Level Interactions'),
