  ('The_Lighthouse', 230, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   230  3.7.8   Technical Infrastructure  Name   Link  Techni  cal  Asset  Details  https://sso.internal.eportal.mastercard.int/pgmctg - prod - portal/program - catalog -  ui/#/technical - assets/5500/details  Reposit  ory  https://scm.mastercard.int/stash/projects/ALBERTA/repos/consumer - service/browse  Postma  n  Collecti  on  https://scm.mastercard.int/stash/projects/ALBERTA/repos/postman -  tests/browse/consumer - service/Consumer - Service.postman_collection.json  Oracle  Databa  se  https://confluence.mastercard.int/pages/viewpage.action?spaceKey=alberta&title=Atla  s+Onboarding#AtlasOnboarding - OracleDatabaseAccess  Secure  d  Access  Policy  https://scm.mastercard.int/stash/projects/SPMADMIN/repos/com - mastercard - digital -  platform_consumer - services/browse  Static  Code  Analysi  s Tool  https://fusion.mastercard.int/sonar/dashboard?branch=dev&id=com.mastercard%3Aco  nsumer - service  Black  Duck  Scan  https://mc.app.blackduck.com/api/search/project -  versions?limit=100&offset=0&q=consumer%20service  3.7.9   Team and ALM  •   Team:  Mastercard Checkout Services   -   Team Composition  •   ALM Current Iteration Status:  https://rally1.rallydev.com/#/192734534488d/iterationstatus  •   Prod Support Escalation:  Atlas Escalation  •   Iteration Planning Board:  Atlas (Consumer and Installments) › Iteration Planning | Rally  •   Team ALM Board:  Atlas (Consumer and Installments) › Team Board | Rally  •   Team Retrospective:  <Confluence Reference>  •   Open Defects:  <JIRA/ALM Reference>'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 231, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   231  3.7.10   Get Profile by External Consumer Id  Test  Case Id  Summary   Behavior   Comments  Success Response  TC_001   Verify 200 OK when mandatory and all  optional fields are provided  Given a get consumer  request is received by the  directory  When all mandatory fields are  present and valid + all  optional fields are valid.  And the get consumer API is  called,  Then the system must return  HTTP 200 OK  TC_002   Verify that a 200 OK response in  returned when CredentialService returns  no credential found  Given valid consumer fetched  When CredentialService  returns returns empty list  Then the system must return  HTTP 200 OK  TC_003   Verify that a 200 OK response is  returned for a credential with no address  present  Given a get consumer profile  request is received by the  directory  When a credential has no  address present  Then the system must return  HTTP 200 OK  Field Robustness (Null / Empty / Spaces / Invalid / Boundary)  TC_004  Verify that a 400 Bad Request response  is returned when INVALID_ARGUMENT  when externalConsumerId has invalid  format.  Given a get consumer profile  request is received by the  directory  When externalConsumerId  has invalid UUID format  Then the system must reject  the request and return HTTP  400 Bad Request  TC_005  Verify that a 400 Bad Request response  is returned when INVALID_ARGUMENT  when srcClientId is missing.  Given a get consumer profile  request is received by the  directory  When srcClientId is missing.  Then the system must reject  the request and return HTTP  400 Bad Request  TC_006   Verify that a 400 Bad Request response  is returned when INVALID_ARGUMENT  when externalConsumerId is missing.  Given a get consumer profile  request is received by the  directory  When externalConsumerId is  missing.  Then the system must reject  the request and return HTTP  400 Bad Request'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 232, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   232  Test  Case Id  Summary   Behavior   Comments  TC_007   Verify that a 400 Bad Request response  is returned when INVALID_ARGUMENT  when directoryId is missing.  Given a get consumer profile  request is received by the  directory  When when directoryId is  missing.  Then the system must reject  the request and return HTTP  400 Bad Request  Not Found  TC_008   Verify that a 404 NOT_FOUND response  is returned when consumer profile does  not exist.  Given a get consumer profile  request is received by the  directory  When consumer profile  doesnt exist  Then the system must reject  the request and return HTTP  404 Bad Request  client lacks permission.  TC_009   Verify that a 403 response is returned  when client configuration is missing in  TCS  Given a get consumer profile  request is received by the  directory  When the client configuration  is missing in TCS  Then the system must reject  the request and return HTTP  403 Forbidden  TC_010   Verify 403 when directory configuration  not found in TCS  Given a get consumer profile  request is received by the  directory  When directory configuration  not found in TCS  Then the system must reject  the request and return HTTP  403 Forbidden  TC_011   Verify 403 for cross - client access  (directoryId not owned by client)  Given a get consumer profile  request is received by the  directory  When the directoryId not  owned by client  Then the system must reject  the request and return HTTP  403 Forbidden  3.8   Middleware Service Dashboard  3.8.1   Table of Contents  •   Overview  •   Dependencies'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 233, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   233  •   Endpoints & behavior  o   Swagger   -   <update link to swagger>  ▪   B2B endpoint  ▪   Confirmations endpoint  ▪   Composite checkout endpoint  •   Service Capabilities and configurations  •   High - Level Interaction Diagrams  •   Current Performance Metrics  •   Technical Roadmap  •   Technical Infrastructure  •   Team and ALM  3.8.2   Overview  •   Description:  Middleware is a program sensitive orchestration service within the MACS that manages  appropriate operations to complete the Checkout successfully.  o   This orchestration service is primarily responsible for handling the creation of  payload with in the MACs system with the Dynamic Data Cryptogram or DTVC  for secure transactions. It comprises of other services like Composite Checkout  Service and Credential   Dispatcher Service. It interacts with other downstream  platform services and does the validation of the request based on the program  rules configured for the different clients and serves the payload.  o   Composite Checkout Service is a super orchestration layer that is built  specifically for Apple Batch Checkout use cases. It calls the profile for enroll as  well the Checkout based on the request type.  o   Credentials Dispatcher Service is responsible for pushing the payload to BND  asynchronously and BND would in turn call the third party SRCI using the Make  Payment API.  o   SRC Core (Code name   -   Alberta) is a EMVCo standards - based checkout  solution for browser - based & in - app payments, providing a consistent  consumer journey for ecommerce, where every card is secured through  network tokenization and every transaction is authen ticated through 3 - D  Secure. SRC is built upon EMVCo industry standards including the EMV®  Secure Remote Commerce Technical Framework (SRC), the EMV® Payment  Tokenization Specification   –   Technical Framework, and the updated EMV® 3 - D  Secure Protocol and Core   Functions Specification.  o   This browser - based checkout is usually referred as Clickto - Pay (C2P). C2P  provides a comprehensive set of checkout services including (but not limited to)  performing the role of a Digital Card Facilitator (DCF) and SRCi, providing a  Mastercard implementati on that integrates with the SRC System(s), allows for  authentication of the cardholder and opportunity for the merchant to obtain  fraud liability shift to the issuer, enables the creation and storage of a Payment  Token, generated by either the Mastercard D igital Enablement Service (MDES)  or an approved Third -   Party Token Service Provider (TSP), including use of  dynamic data in each transaction to enforce token domain restriction controls,  exposes secure interfaces to Digital Shopping Applications (DSAs) suc h as  Merchants, and SRC Initiators such as Payment Service Providers to perform'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 234, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   234  payments, and provides consistent user experiences for checkout including the  display of issuer card art.  o   Apart from supporting browser - based eCommerce checkout transactions, SRC  also enables Merchants & other clients to use Card - On - File (COF) for  checkouts. This feature is generally referred as SCOF   - Secure Card - On - File.  All of our SCOF functions are exposed   to our clients via B2B APIs, that are  protected either using MTLS or OAuth.  ▪   The clients that use this function are broadly classified into 2 types:  •   • S4C   –   SRC for Device based clients ( etc. Apple Pay)  •   •   S4M   –   SRC for Merchants / Processors (Adyen / Paypal)  o   Both C2P & SCOF flows tie into the Mastercard Authorization flow via a  component called Merchant Binding & Verification Service (aka MBVS). MBVS  is a PCF app, that is part of the SRC ecosystem, which binds Merchants with  Cryptograms / Tokens submitted by A cquirers. The main purpose of this  binding is to improve fraud detection by ensuring that the token / cryptograms in  the transaction belong to the Merchant.  o   SCOF flows produce certain notification events that are pushed to the clients  using a component called Business Notification Dispatcher (BND). BND is  another PCF app, that is part of SRC ecosystem, which notifies the client on  these events. Some of the cri tical events sent back to the clients are: • NTU  (Notify Token Update)   –   A card lifecycle update event (such as card  successfully tokenized, or card reported as lost etc.) • TDS (Transaction Detail  Service)   –   A TDS event is triggered when a enrolled / toke nized card is used for  a transaction.  •   Purpose & Scope: <UPDATE>  o  3.8.3   Dependencies  This table lists and describes all services or systems that provide input or trigger events for this  microservice or rely on data or functionalities from this microservice.  Service Name   Type   Service Dashboard  Pre - Checkout   Upstream  Middleware   Upstream  Composite Checkout   Upstream  External Clients (e.g. MCI,MPGS, POP)   Upstream  TCS   Downstream  PI Core   Downstream  Consumer Service   Downstream'),
