  ('The_Lighthouse', 238, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   238  3.9   Payment Instrument Service Dashboard  3.9.1   Table of Contents  •   Overview  •   Dependencies  •   Endpoints & Supported Use Cases  o   Endpoints Overview  o   Supported Use Cases by Endpoint  •   High - Level Interaction Diagrams  •   Service Level Agreements (SLAs)  •   Current Performance Metrics  •   Future Projections  •   Technical Roadmap  3.9.2   Overview  •   Description:  Payment instrument service is a program agnostic MACS platform service which manages  cards and token (storage provisioning and lifecycle). It also offers transaction  credentials and lookup operations. Payment instrument integrates with the backend  systems   like MDES, BNC, CAAS, ABU, PAM for MACS.  •   Purpose and scope  Payment instrument servers to orchestration services of MACS, to perform use cases like  card enrolment, token generation and card/token lifecycle event processing. It securely  stores and manages cards, tokens and other payment instruments.  3.9.3   Dependencies  This table lists and describes all services or systems that provide input or trigger events for this  microservice or rely on data or functionalities from this microservice.  Service Name   Type   Service Dashboard  Pre - Checkout   Upstream  Profile   Upstream  Push Provisioning   Upstream  Authentication Service / Platform   Upstream  Checkout   Upstream  MDES (Mastercard Digital enablement services)   Downstream  Banknet Connect (Pre - Digi ISO APIs)   Downstream  MPS (Member Parameter Service)   Downstream'),
