  ('The_Lighthouse', 247, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   247  Behav  ior Id  Title   Behavior   Chan  ge  Log  Comments  refType=''TOKEN_UNIQUE_R  EFERENCE '' & valid  programId  Then   HTTP 200 response  must be provided with all the  account range details as per  specification.  3.10   Pre - Checkout Service Dashboard  3.10.1   Table of Contents  •   Overview  •   Dependencies  •   Endpoints & behavior  o   Swagger   -   <update link to swagger>  ▪   POST /identities/lookup  ▪   POST /identities/verification  ▪   POST /identities/validation  ▪   POST /customerProfiles  ▪   POST /checkout/identities/lookup  ▪   POST /identities/validation/initiate  ▪   POST /identities/validation/complete  ▪   POST /profiles/prepare  ▪   POST /transactionCredentials  ▪   POST /bind  ▪   POST /cards  •   Service Capabilities and configurations  •   High - Level Interaction Diagrams  •   Current Performance Metrics  •   Technical Roadmap  •   Technical Infrastructure  •   Team and ALM  3.10.2   Overview  •   Description:  Pre - checkout is a program agnostic orchestration service within the MACS initially built to  support   Click - to - Pay (C2P) checkout   operations by adhering the EMVCo guidelines.'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 248, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   248  o   This orchestration service is primarily responsible for identifying the existence  of C2P profiles, performing OTP, retrieving the profiles'' card list by interacting  various downstream services. This operation might be triggered from a variety  of services a nd pre - checkout returns the data to the relevant upstream service.  o   Pre - checkout is enhanced to support different programs besides SRC such as  OPEN_BANKING and P2P Payments.  o   For browser - based checkout which is usually referred as C2P checkout, p re -  checkout supports both UCS and MCS requests. Pre - checkout doesn''t apply  different rules to UCS or MCS requests.  o   Pre - checkout currently supports B2B and B2C operations.  ▪   B2C known as a C2P checkout starts from the merchants browser /  native app.  ▪   B2B known as Connected Credentials, can leverage the checkouts  where   Digital Card Facilitator (DCF) is limited or not in place. This is  achieved by integrators establishing direct API integrations with Pre -  checkout B2B APIs.  •   Purpose & Scope:  o   Pre - checkout serves to upstream services by communicating with various  downstream services. The ultimate purpose is providing merchants/integrators  and their consumers a secure and easy checkout process (for both B2B and  B2C) by  ▪   identifying an existing consumer in C2P system  ▪   initiating and completing the consumer authentication  ▪   providing the existing card list of the consumers  3.10.3   Dependencies  This table lists and describes all services or systems that provide input or trigger events for this  microservice or rely on data or functionalities from this microservice.  Review the table with Tarun  Service Name   Type   Service Dashboard  DCF   Upstream   DCF Service Dashboard   -   Alberta   -   Confluence  SDK   Upstream   N/A  B2B Integrator   Upstream   N/A  TCS   Downstream   N/A  PI Core   Downstream   Payment Instrument