  ('The_Lighthouse', 264, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   264  Behavior Id   Title   Behavior   Change Log  consumer - id  with some  different value  than the one  from the  request  Then   reject the request  and return the  response as 400 bad  request  dir - cns - cre - con.006.create -  consumer.companion.multi - pii -  consumer.conflicts.external -  consumer - id - and - identities  PROPOSED  This scenario is  possible only during  migration from single  to multi PII due to the  data being available  in both the structures  based on DUAL  WRITE solution of  SID epic  Companion Program  - Multi PII Consumer  request with  external - consumer - id  and identities :  external - consumer - id  doesn''t conflict with  existing profiles but  Identities conflict with  existing profile and  that profile''s  external - consumer - id  is null  Given   a multi PII  consumer creation  request is received for  a   companion program  with external -  consumer - id and  identities  When  1.   the consumer  service doesn''t  find a match on  external -  consumer - id  within the same  directory  2.   and some or all  of the identities  match on the  same single  profile  3.   and matched  profile doesn''t  have the  external -  consumer - id  (NULL)  Then   return the 409  conflict with conflict  type as ''IDENTITIES''.  Include consumer  object in the response.  1.   MCSE -  330 [SID] :  Support  Flexible  enrollment  into issuer  directory with  partial PII  [SID]  3.10.12   Pre - checkout   - Use cases identities/validation  •   Returning user flow   -   C2P cards only'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 265, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   265  3.10.12.1   B2C Returning User  Use  Case  Number  Coverage   Use Case  Title  Description   Use Case Details   E2E  Tests  PCU1   Critical   B2C  Returning  user flow   -  C2P cards  only  GIVEN   the  consumer is  verified and card  List returned  successfully  WHEN   the  consumer selects  one of the cards  from the card list  THEN   the  consumer can  complete the  checkout  successfully.  1.Merchant / Integrator looks  up for the consumer via email  or phone number  POST /identities/lookup  2. OTP message is sent to the  consumer  POST /identities/verification  3. Consumer successfully  completes the OTP  POST /identities/validation  4. Card List successfully  returns to the merchant /  integrator  POST /customerProfiles  5. Consumer selects a card  from the card list and proceed  to checkout  6. Consumer completes the  checkout successfully.  POST  /transactionCredentials  PCU2  3.11   Profile Service Dashboard  3.11.1   Table of Contents  •   Overview  •   Dependencies  •   Endpoints & behavior  o   Swagger   -   <update link to swagger>'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 266, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   266  •   Service Capabilities and configurations  •   High - Level Interaction Diagrams  •   Current Performance Metrics  •   Technical Roadmap  •   Technical Infrastructure  •   Team and ALM  3.11.2   Overview  •   Description:  Checkout Service is a program sensitive orchestration service within the MACS that  manages appropriate Checkout payload composition. ...... <Add overview>  •   Purpose & Scope: <UPDATE>  o   As a platform service, it delivers significant business value to MACS by  supporting various flows such as B2C (Click To Pay) and B2B (SCOF).  o   It also offers separate directories for each issuer, enhancing trust and  compliance. This allows issuers to securely onboard consumer data and  enables MACS to provide auto - enrolment solutions where issuers remain in  control of their data.  o   Additionally, the MACS supports third - party wallets (e.g. Samsung) by allowing  wallets to provision consumer and wallet information in the directory. This  enables the presentation of wallet credentials during a payment experience and  facilitates seamless l inking or redirection to the Wallet interface when a  consumer selects a wallet for payment.  3.11.3   Dependencies  This table lists and describes all services or systems that provide input or trigger events for this  microservice or rely on data or functionalities from this microservice.  Service Name   Type   Service Dashboard  Pre - Checkout   Upstream  Push Provisioning   Upstream  Profile   Upstream  Account Management Service   Upstream  Checkout   Upstream  Consumer Scheduler   Upstream  CaaS   Downstream  <Diagram   Neeraj Dase   can help generate>'),
