  ('The_Lighthouse', 270, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   270  <service level configurations>  3.11.6   High - Level Interaction Diagrams  •   Sequence Diagrams:   Consumer Service API Diagrams  •   ER Diagram :   profile Service ER Diagram  •   Component interaction   -  •   Data Model:  3.11.7   Current Performance Metrics  •   Metrics:  Consumer Service Production Statistics .  •   Monitoring:  o   Link to Dynatrace dashboards   -  ▪   Global   -   Consumer Service Insights  ▪   Pune   -   Consumer Service https://sft042.dynatrace -  managed.com/e/95d25318 - 8269 - 4c27 - a2e3 -  e83f8a22c4ab/#dashboard;gtf=yesterday;gf=all;id=28eb163e - 05b2 -  4c74 - 8c2d - 43ce70e0c63b;applyDashboardDefaults=true Insights  ▪   MACS Service Availability  o   SRE Alerts  ▪   Consumer Service Alerts  3.11.8   Technical Roadmap  •   Atlas Tech Debt Tracker   -   Alberta   -   Confluence  •   profile Service technical roadmap  3.11.9   Technical Infrastructure  Name   Link  Techni  cal  Asset  Details  https://sso.internal.eportal.mastercard.int/pgmctg - prod - portal/program - catalog -  ui/#/technical - assets/5500/details  Reposit  ory  https://scm.mastercard.int/stash/projects/ALBERTA/repos/consumer - service/browse  Postma  n  Collecti  on  https://scm.mastercard.int/stash/projects/ALBERTA/repos/postman -  tests/browse/consumer - service/Consumer - Service.postman_collection.json'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 271, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   271  Name   Link  Oracle  Databa  se  https://confluence.mastercard.int/pages/viewpage.action?spaceKey=alberta&title=Atla  s+Onboarding#AtlasOnboarding - OracleDatabaseAccess  Secure  d  Access  Policy  https://scm.mastercard.int/stash/projects/SPMADMIN/repos/com - mastercard - digital -  platform_consumer - services/browse  Static  Code  Analysi  s Tool  https://fusion.mastercard.int/sonar/dashboard?branch=dev&id=com.mastercard%3Aco  nsumer - service  Black  Duck  Scan  https://mc.app.blackduck.com/api/search/project -  versions?limit=100&offset=0&q=consumer%20service  3.11.10   Team and ALM  •   Team:  Mastercard Checkout Services   -   Team Composition  •   ALM Current Iteration Status:  https://rally1.rallydev.com/#/192734534488d/iterationstatus  •   Prod Support Escalation:  Atlas Escalation  •   Iteration Planning Board:  Atlas (Consumer and Installments) › Iteration Planning | Rally  •   Team ALM Board:  Atlas (Consumer and Installments) › Team Board | Rally  •   Open Defects:  Atlas Owned Defects  3.11.11   Stage Environment'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 272, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  MACS Services   –   272  3.11.12   profile Service technical roadmap  Sr.  No.  Title   Description   Priority  1   Plain text PII data in  external_account_id  Previously, the profile service incorrectly sent consumers''  email addresses in the external_account field to the  consumer service for companion programs (when  Identity_Type was EMAIL). As this field was not designed  for PII, it stored these emails in plain   text. The profile  service fixed the defect on their side and now sends a null  value when Identity_Type is EMAIL, but existing plain text  data remains in the consumer domain and needs a  remediation.  High'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 273, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  Domains and Platform   –   273  4   Domains and Platform  4.1   Actors  •   Actor   -   Consumer  •   Actor   -   Directory Provider  •   Actor   -   Identity Provider  •   Actor   -   Integrator  •   Actor   -   Issuer  •   Actor   -   Merchant  4.2   API Integration  4.3   Architecture  4.4   Data principle  •   On - Soil and localization  •   PCI data protection  •   PII data protection  4.5   Domains capabilities  •   Checkout Domain Sample  •   Enrollment   -   Domain  •   On boarding  4.6   MACS Attribute dictionary  4.7   Programs definitions and principles  4.8   Actors  •   Actor   -   Consumer  •   Actor   -   Directory Provider  •   Actor   -   Identity Provider  •   Actor   -   Integrator  •   Actor   -   Issuer  •   Actor   -   Merchant'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 274, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  Domains and Platform   –   274  4.8.1   Actor   -   Consumer  4.8.2   Actor   -   Directory Provider  4.8.3   Actor   -   Identity Provider  4.8.4   Actor   -   Integrator  4.8.5   Actor   -   Issuer  4.8.6   Actor   -   Merchant  4.9   API Integration  4.10   Architecture  4.10.1   Vision  4.10.2   Principle  4.10.3   Deployment  4.11   Data principle  4.11.1   On - Soil and localization  4.11.2   PCI data protection  4.11.3   PII data protection  4.12   Domains capabilities  4.12.1   Checkout Domain Sample  4.12.2   Enrollment   -   Domain  4.12.2.1   Overview  •   Purpose : What business or technical problem does this domain solve?  •   Boundaries : What is in scope and out of scope? Bounded Context  •   Stakeholders : Who owns or consumes this domain?'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 275, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  Domains and Platform   –   275  4.12.2.2   Capabilities  •   Core Capabilities : Consumer, Card enrollment and token provisioning,  •   Supporting Capabilities : card holder verification  1   enrols card in to MACS program  2   enrols card in to MACS program, provisions cloud, static token if card is eligible for  tokenization  3   enrols consumer and card in to MACS program, generates cloud, static token if card is  eligible for tokenization  4   enrols cards in bulk  5   enrols existing tokens in MACS program  4.12.3   On boarding  Client Onboarding  Merchant Onboarding  4.13   MACS Attribute dictionary  A repository of all the attributes/params that are part of MACS API/Swaggers  Don''t reinvent the wheel Feel free to reuse it  Addition/update   must   be done with co - ordination Architecture, Product Development and  Documentation  Fiel  d  nam  e  Data  type  Form  at  Siz  e  Intern  al  only  Y/N  Standard  version   -  EMVCo/W3  C?  Sampl  e  Descripti  on  Notes/Commen  ts  Change  History   -  Feature/Sto  ry #  First  Nam  e  Strin  g  4.14   Programs definitions and principles'),
  ('The_Lighthouse', 276, 'Alberta   –   The Lighthouse  Programs and Products   –   276  5   Programs and Products  5.1   Click2Pay  5.2   Click - to - Pay Push Provisioning  5.3   Guest Checkout tokenization  5.4   SCOF   -   VCN   -   Auto form fill  5.5   To be re - purposed for C2P  5.6   RACI Matrix (Product dimension)  RACI Matrix [Product dimension]  The RACI matrix is a powerful tool used to define roles and responsibilities. It stands for  Responsible, Accountable, Consulted, and Informed. Here we delve into the definitions  and significance of each role and ownership of various artifacts within produc t dimension.  RACI Roles Explained  •   Responsible   (R):   The person or people who   do the work   to complete the task.  •   Accountable   (A):   The one person who is   ultimately answerable for the task''s  completion and quality ;   they sign off on the work  •   Consulted   (C):   Subject matter experts   whose input is needed   (two - way  communication) to ensure the task is done correctly.  •   Informed   (I):   Stakeholders or others who need to be   kept in the loop   on progress  and outcomes (one - way communication).  Artifact   Place   PM   Architect   Sample  1   Product overview   section   A/R   C   Guest Checkout  tokenization   -   Alberta   -  Confluence  2   product Construct   section   A/R   C   Guest Checkout  tokenization   -   Alberta   -  Confluence  3   Actor and Workflow   section   A/R   C   Guest Checkout  tokenization   -   Alberta   -  Confluence'),
